title: bean curd "duck"
directions: Soak bean curd in water overnight.
Wash in clear water.
Cook bean curd until tender in 1 cup water, oil, onion, coriander, soy sauce, ginger, garlic and salt.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix 3 packages of cream cheese; let it thaw until soft.
Mix all the ingredients and make it in a ball.
Chill 1 hour and top with chopped pecans or sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate until you serve.

title: ritz pie
directions: Beat egg whites in mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Add sugar, baking powder and vanilla gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in crushed crackers and chopped walnuts.
Spoon into an 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool.
Garnish with whipped topping.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: sour cream macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; rinse in cold water and drain. Place in a large bowl; add green pepper, pickle relish, pimentos and onion. In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour over macaroni mixture and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate until serving. Serves 6.

title: egg-cheese pie (quiche)
directions: Put pie shell in
pie
plate.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper in blender.
Put
in
pie
shell.
Drop Cheddar and ham (or bacon) into egg
mixture.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes and at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: waffle cookies
directions: Mix butter, eggs and sugar together.
Add vanilla; beat well. Add flour.
Drop by spoonfuls onto hot waffle iron.
Cook until done.
(I usually cut recipe in half!)

title: date - nuts squares
directions: Layer as listed.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Let cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except lettuce and tomatoes.
Let chill 1 hour.
When ready to serve, toss with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: nacho-supreme
directions: Brown meat.
Add pepper and onion when half done.
Stir in taco seasoning and cilantro.
Spread beans in thin layer in a 12-inch pizza pan or jelly roll pan.
Spread meat mixture over beans.
Drizzle with 1/2 taco sauce; top with both cheeses. Drizzle with remaining taco sauce.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with unseasoned tortilla chips.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place deboned chicken in bottom of 1 pie shell.
Mix together sour cream, margarine, cream of chicken, onions and mixed vegetables.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Season to taste.
Place second pie shell on top.
Use a fork and go around the edge of pie.
Cut 3 to 4 vents on top of pie.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: erika's cinnamon toast
directions: Set oven on broil and high.
Take desired slices of bread and spread soft margarine over slices, then sprinkle liberal amount of sugar on bread.
Next take cinnamon and sprinkle on lightly to medium depending on taste.
Toast until edges brown.

title: quick orange blueberry muffins
directions: This is more a trick than a recipe.
Follow the directions on any muffin mix but substitute orange juice for the recommended amount of water.
This gives the muffin a nice, tangy taste that goes well with sweet blueberry taste.
It works especially well with "light" muffin mixes which tend to be less tasty when made as directed.
And, if you prefer making muffins from scratch, this substitution works well! Oven temperature:
Time:
15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 12.

title: irene's scalloped potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in layers in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle each layer with onion, salt and pepper; dot with margarine.
Add hot milk.
Microwave on 60 (Bake) for 35 minutes. Cover with lid or wax paper for best results.

title: salmon loaf with lemon butter dill sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Add salmon.
Mix until uniform.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 3/4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until center is firm.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before removing from pan.
Slice and serve with Dill Sauce, steaming white rice and English peas.

title: spuds elegant
directions: Blend cheese and egg into potatoes.
Add remaining ingredients, except paprika.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 6.

title: pork chops and dressing
directions: Place pork chops, celery rib, salt and onion in large saucepan with 4 cups water and butter.
Let come to a boil; then reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, flour, seasoning and vanilla flavoring.
Beat well, then mix well with all chopped fruit.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 12 to 20 minutes.

title: curried tomato soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion and garlic in hot oil until tender. Add curry powder; cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Add tomatoes, broth, fines herbes, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Cool slightly.
In a food processor or blender container, cover and process cooled mixture, half at a time, until smooth.
If desired, press through a sieve.
Serve hot or chilled.
If desired, top with yogurt, fresh thyme and quartered cherry tomatoes.
Makes 6 dishes.

title: my grandma's potato salad
directions: In large bowl combine potatoes, olives, pickles and eggs. Fold dressing in and add salt and pepper.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Beat in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini and flour with cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Add nuts; pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake in 350° oven in 9 x 5-inch loaf pans for 1 hour.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: fresh peach muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine with a few drops of almond flavoring.
Add peaches and beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour.
Work mixture quickly but do not overmix.
Pour mixture into 18 greased muffin cups.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top of muffin batter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Yields 18 muffins.

title: grandma's fudge
directions: In a large cook pot, add all ingredients except peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Cook on medium-high.
Once boiling, continue for about 10 to 13 additional minutes, until hard ball stage in water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Place in well buttered pie pans.
Can also be placed in cookie tins.
Makes two containers.
Be sure to cook long enough or you'll end up with spoon fudge.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Stew chicken until done.
Do not salt.
Pull off bones and set aside, saving the broth.
Stir together dressing mixes, chopped onion and melted margarine.
In a greased 13 x 9-inch dish, put a layer of dressing, a layer of chicken and
then a layer of mushroom soup, diluted with a can of broth.
Add another layer of crumbs (dressing), a layer of chicken and a can of chicken soup, diluted with a can of broth.
End with a layer of crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown, approximately 1 hour.
(This may be cut in half for 2 people.)

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook carrots, cauliflower and broccoli.
Place in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cube 1/2 pound of Velveeta cheese and mix with vegetables.
Slice remaining cheese and place on top.
Place Ritz crackers, rolled and crumbled on top.
Melt oleo and drizzle over. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Beat 10 minutes. Store in refrigerator for up to 2 weeks. If you want an ivory colored frosting, use butter flavored Crisco.

title: colorful jello salad
directions: Begin by making one package at a time, starting with one flavor Jell-O.
One layer will be clear and one layer will be milky.
If you start with milky layer, you will finish with clear layer.

title: sugar-free vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer.
While freezer is turning, add crushed ice and thawing salt.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Time:
Approximately 30 minutes.

title: seafood spread
directions: Soften cream cream cheese with lemon juice.
Add shrimp, crabmeat and green onions to cream cheese mixture.
Add enough mayonnaise to give a consistency for spreading on crackers. Season with hot sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Better if made 8 hours ahead of time.
Serves 15.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add ginger ale when you are ready to serve punch.
You can make an ice ring by filling Bundt pan with water and freeze.
Will probably serve 150.

title: donna's peanut butter doo-dads
directions: Stir in large pan 1 cup sugar, 1 cup Karo syrup and jar of peanut butter.
Stir over medium heat until soft and mixed well. Remove from heat and add cereal.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Saute ground turkey with onion and green pepper.
Add taco seasoning mix, tomato sauce and water.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: christmas pecan cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour Bundt or tube pan.
Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Combine flour and baking powder. Combine milk and vanilla.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk to creamed mixture, beating smoothly after adding.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually beat in remaining 1/2 cup sugar until stiff, but not dry.
Fold whites gently into batter.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until wooden pick is withdrawn clean. Frost with cream cheese icing.

title: farmer's salad
directions: Dice all vegetables medium fine and shred carrots and cabbage. Toss all vegetables together lightly.
Add tomatoes last.
Serve with French or Thousand Island dressing.
Put dressing on when served and not before.

title: quick taco bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and onions; drain fat.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Stir in dry seasoning mix, tomato sauce and corn.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: mexican dip
directions: Roll 1/2 strip of bacon around large stuffed green olive. Broil 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Put pineapple juice and sugar in a saucepan and cook for 5 minutes after it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add jello and cream cheese.
When completely cooled, fold into whipped milk. Pour and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan and chill completely in refrigerator.

title: mock mincemeat(green tomato)
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bring to boil, then simmer until thick. Cool and place in freezer cartons.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, then the molasses.
Add the dry ingredients (sifted together).
Mix well. Add oatmeal and raisins last.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes on greased cookie sheets.

title: broccoli parmesan
directions: Cook frozen broccoli spears in unsalted water until tender. Drain.
Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in cream of chicken soup, milk and cheese.
Heat and serve atop broccoli. Serves 6.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients into a pan.
Mix together.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake at 350°.

title: chicken and green beans
directions: Cut chicken into cubes (approximately 1-inch).
Mix first 5 ingredients to create soy sauce mixture; set aside.
Heat large skillet on medium; add oil.
Stir-fry beans about 2 minutes. Remove beans.
Add chicken to skillet (additional oil if necessary).
Cook chicken about 10 minutes.
Add beans and soy sauce.
Stir almost continually until thick and bubbly.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken liver and potato bake
directions: In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
In hot skillet drippings, cook chicken livers until browned, about 5 minutes, turning once.
Arrange bacon and chicken livers in 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole.
Pour undiluted onion soup over liver mixture.

title: my favorite fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
In a
large bowl, mix all ingredients together.
Add 2 or 3 drops red food coloring.
Mix well. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: duck gumbo
directions: Boil ducks in salt, pepper and 1 onion.
Take off bone and save 2 quarts of stock.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring butter, brown sugar, salt and Karo light syrup to a boil, stirring.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir 5 times.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
Pour in one or two shallow baking pans.
Bake at 150° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: soft raisin cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs. In small pan, add raisins and soda to water. Bring to a boil. When raisins float, remove from heat and cool 10 to 15 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° about 10 minutes.

title: brown sugar squares
directions: Blend egg, sugar and vanilla.
Do not beat.
Quickly stir in flour and add nuts.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: very strawberry pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cubes and stir until melted.
Prepare pie filling mix with milk as for a pie; let stand about 2 minutes.
Blend in gelatin. Chill, if necessary, until thickened.
Fold in 2 cups of the whipped topping and strawberries.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 1 hour or chill in refrigerator 3 hours before serving.
Garnish with remaining topping and strawberries.

title: cardinal salad
directions: Combine vinegar and oil well and toss with ingredients.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix well with dressing mix.
Grease pan with margarine.
Put layer of dressing mix on bottom of large casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 of chicken over mix.
Dilute mushroom soup with 1 can of chicken broth from boiled chicken. Pour over the chicken.
Add another layer of chicken.
Add can of cream of chicken soup which has been diluted with can of chicken broth.
Top with layer of dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch oven dish.
Thaw potatoes and place in casserole.
Mix other ingredients, except for crumbs, and pour over potatoes.
Top with the cracker crumbs.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
May be made ahead and baked when needed.

title: the best ever roast
directions: Take your roast and brown it in a little oil on top of your stove.
Then take the mushroom soup and half a can of water and combine them in a crock-pot.
Then splash on your roast and into the pot some Worcestershire sauce, add salt, pepper and Tony's.

title: chocolate pecan pralines
directions: Mix sugar, Pet milk and cocoa.
Cook ingredients for 15 to 20 minutes on simmer and stir constantly until mixture gets hard. Test with cold water.
Add butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla extract.
Cook for about 5 minutes until mixture boils for a few minutes.
Add pecans and cook for about 3 minutes until pecans get warm.
Spoon onto buttered pans.

title: broccoli-cheese bites
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Steam broccoli (5 minutes) partially cooked.
Drain well.
Beat eggs in large bowl. Add flour, salt, milk and baking powder.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese, onion and drained broccoli.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°, until corners are browned.

title: blueberry dessert pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: baby stuffed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes, unpeeled, in water until just done (do not overcook). Drain and cool. Scoop out the top portion of the potatoes and mash thoroughly. Add the sour cream and blend. Add the dressing mix and stir well. Place some of the mixture into the potato cavities and garnish with paprika.

title: holiday punch
directions: Add jello to 2 cups boiling water in large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen juices.
Stir until well blended.
Add 6 cups cold water and pineapple juice; mix well.
Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 50 servings.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually add sugar and vanilla, beating well.
Stir in candy coating and pecans.
Spread into a buttered 8-inch square pan; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into small squares.
Yields 2 pounds.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a
large
saucepan; stir well. Place over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves. Then cook to soft ball stage (about 232°).
Remove from
heat; add pecans, stirring until
well
coated.
Spread pecans
on waxed
paper and separate nuts with
a
fork.
Let cool.
Yields 2 cups.

title: turtle bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender.
Cover container and blend well on low speed for about 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm or cool and, if desired, sprinkle with nutmeg.
This pie makes its own crust.

title: chocolate or vanilla clusters
directions: Melt bark as directed on package (microwave best way to go in 1 1/2 minutes).
Pour in bowl and stir in peanut butter and then add Rice Krispies, marshmallows and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheets with wax paper on.
I used 4 cookie sheets.
Chill 10 to 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Can be stored in refrigerator or freezer.
Very delicious and easy to make.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Place muffin halves on large baking sheet sprayed with a cooking spray.
Combine last 6 ingredients together for sauce.
Spread over the halves of muffins.
Sprinkle the meat of your choice over the sauce.
Sprinkle the cheese over the meat.
Place in heated oven.
Bake until cheese is well melted (about 15 minutes).

title: chocolate crusted pie
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a mixing bowl. Cut in shortening.
Combine cold water and vanilla and sprinkle over mixture, stirring with fork until dough is moist enough to hold together.

Form into a ball. Roll out on floured surface to a circle 1 1/2 inches larger than inverted 9-inch pie pan. Fit loosely into pan. Fold edge to form a standing rim; flute. Prick generously. Place "trimmings" in second pan.
Bake pie shell and trimmings at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Crumble trimmings for crumb topping.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in flour and chips.
Add nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet in approximately 1 rounded teaspoonfuls.
Cook at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: savory carrot salad(serves 6)
directions: About 1 hour before serving, in medium bowl, toss together all ingredients, but lettuce.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour to "marry" flavors.
To serve, divide salad among lettuce cups.
Has 75 calories per serving.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; mix in order listed.
Pour into mold or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles according to directions. Drain.
In large bowl, toss noodles with Ricotta (or cottage cheese), Mozzarella and Parmesan.
In two-quart oblong baking dish, spoon enough sauce to cover bottom.
Layer half the noodles mixture and half the sauce.
Repeat.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Makes about four servings.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: tuna mac salad
directions: Combine drained/cooked macaroni with well drained tuna.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve chilled on lettuce with tomato wedges and favorite cracker.

title: minestrone
directions: Saute onion, potato and carrot in oil until onion is golden brown and soft.
Add water, oregano, basil, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add zucchini and boil additional 15 minutes.
Add beans, tomatoes and macaroni and boil 12-15 minutes or until macaroni is cooked.
For variety, substitute chicken broth for water and add leftover cooked chicken or favorite herbs.

title: funnel cake
directions: Add almond extract and vanilla extract to cake mix.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, including yeast, but use only 1/3 of the flour.
Mix all wet ingredients, including shortening, and heat to hot-warm.
Combine and mix with mixer for two minutes. Add eggs and more flour to thicken.
Mix a couple of minutes. Add rest of flour.

title: oatmeal cookie
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, salt, soda and oatmeal. Can add chocolate chips or raisins.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: potato-date bake
directions: Heat sweet potatoes; mash while hot.
Add cream, cinnamon, salt, dates and butter.
Mix well and turn into a buttered 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pat together firmly and shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until well done.
I usually bake potatoes at the same time.

title: stir and roll single crust
directions: Mix flour.
Pour Wesson oil and milk into cup (don't stir). Add this mixture to flour and stir well.
Press into smooth ball. Flatten slightly and roll.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Brown meat and add onion and cook until transparent.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except flour and mild.
Cover and cook over low heat until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and 1 cup of milk.
Stir into soup mixture and bring to boil.
Add remaining milk and cook 15-20 minutes stirring frequently.
Do not boil, after adding remaining milk.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Cut as many apples as desired, your favorite.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over
apples.	Mix
together 1/2 cup sugar, flour and butter or oleo, until crumbly.
Sprinkle over top of apples, use all
crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: In bowl mix flour, sugar and milk.
In 9 x 13-inch pan melt stick of butter. When butter is bubbling, pour flour batter in center of pan; spread.
In center of pan, pour peaches and half of juice; do not stir.
Cook in 350°
oven for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve warm.

title: linda's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one egg at a time. Add flour alternately with sour cream mixture.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into first mixture.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool in pan.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour into two well-greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° and bake until golden brown. Makes own crust.

title: hot bacon and swiss dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese until soft.
Mix with Miracle Whip, Swiss cheese and onion until well blended.
Spoon in a 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave on High about 4 minutes or until hot.
Sprinkle with bacon crumbs and cracker crumbs.
Serve with pita chips.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Cream together butter and sugar, and add eggs, one at a time, creaming well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, then add vanilla.
Put half of dough in greased and floured 9 X 9 pan, then add half of topping mixture.
Add rest of dough and sprinkle with remaining topping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain and scoop out of shell.
Beat eggs in bowl; add chopped onion, pepper and cheese.
Stir in squash and pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Dot with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can use any cheese, not just Parmesan cheese.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Cream flour, oleo and sugar.
Add pecans.
Press in 9 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool 1 hour.
Cream the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with 1 can cherry pie filling.
Chill and serve.

title: ricotta cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Spoon cheese mixture over cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Powdered sugar can be sprinkled over cake when done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt oleo and pour over herb stuffing crumbs and stir.
Line a 3-quart baking dish with half the crumbs.
Mix other ingredients and pour over bread crumbs.
Put rest of crumbs on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
May be frozen.

title: batter buns
directions: Beat egg into flour and salt.
Add the yeast mixture.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Let raise 1/2 hour and 15 minutes in pan.

title: south carolina pound cake
directions: Using a mixer, cream butter with sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Add the cake flour, a little at a time.
Mix the baking soda and sour cream together and add to mix.
Bake for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes in 325° oven, in a tube pan or until golden brown on top.

title: tuna loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fast eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat broiler. Brush eggplant with olive oil. Sprinkle each slice with a pinch of salt and pepper. Put on baking sheet and broil until cooked through and tender, about 2 to 3 minutes on each side.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cut into mixture the shortening until like coarse meal.
Add buttermilk.

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs and milk well.
Stir in toast, salt, dry mustard and sausage.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add cheese and cook in 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese log
directions: Roll Velveeta between sheets of wax paper to get to a thin sheet.
Spread cream cheese on sheet of Velveeta and cover with green pepper, green onions, olives and pecans.
Roll up.
Keep the roll tight.
Chill in refrigerator before serving.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla, salt and flour.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll in 1 inch balls and bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake mix in jelly roll pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool. Cook until thick the milk and flour (cool completely).
Set aside.

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening.
Add the sugar gradually and continue working until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating about 1 minute after each addition.
Add the apples, cheese and nuts.
Mix well.
Add the dry ingredients in two portions, mixing only until all the flour is dampened.

title: butterscotch crunch top cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix cake mix, pudding and eggs.
Pour into prepared pan. Evenly sprinkle butterscotch chips on top. Then sprinkle chopped walnuts over butterscotch.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream the butter until soft and add the sugar and cream mixture well until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Add the dry ingredients to the creamed mixture alternating the sour cream, beginning and ending with the flour mixture.
Stir in the vanilla.

title: aunt dolores' upside-down ravioli
directions: Cook noodles until tender.
Brown meat, then add spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and tomato paste and simmer for 10 minutes. Cook spinach and drain, reserving 1 cup of drained liquid.
Add this to the meat sauce.
Drain noodles; add cheeses, spinach and 2 beaten eggs.

title: ono flank steak
directions: Combine the shoyu, sugar and garlic.
Soak the flank steak in the marinade for 1 to 2 hours.
Add green onions.
Flour each piece of flank steak and dip into the beaten eggs.
Fry in a small amount of oil until done.
Do not deep fry.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all but the crackers well.
Pour over the crackers, stirring well. They will be glossy at first and then turn dull when ready, about 1 hour.

title: good 'n tender roast
directions: Put all ingredients on top of roast.
Wrap in heavy duty aluminum foil (mix water and lemon; pour over meat).
Cook for 2 hours at 425°.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and beaten eggs. Blend together.
Scald milk and let cool.
Dissolve yeast in water and add to milk.
Add flour to this to form dough. Let set until double.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Let set again to double in size. (Place them in a greased pan as they are made.)
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: fancy potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes and chopped onions in a large pot. Cover with water. Cook until tender. Add the celery soup and the cheese. Stir constantly to keep from sticking. Salt and pepper to taste. Garnish with parsley. Serve with cornbread, muffins or crackers. Delicious.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Toss in oleo to coat thoroughly.
Put in baking dish.
Salt and pepper.
Pour remaining oleo over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water until you have about 1/2 cup water left.
Cream sugar, oleo, egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to flour; add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Wash mushrooms and discard stems; slice thinly.
Place mushrooms and water in a small saucepan.
Bring water to boil and reduce heat.
Cover and steam for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain well. Combine mushrooms, sour cream, mayonnaise, thyme, tarragon, ginger and salt.
Chill until ready to serve.
Spoon over leaf lettuce; sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Boil sugar and syrup together for 2 or 3 minutes. Beat eggs slightly; pour slowly into the hot syrup. Add butter, vanilla and pecan meats. Turn into raw pie shell and bake in moderate oven about 45 minutes or until set.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter.
Coat Rice Chex with chocolate mixture.
Empty 10x sugar into large brown paper grocery bag and dump in coated Chex.
Toss to cover.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix flour, cornmeal, salt, pepper and milk.
Dip sliced tomatoes in batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden.
May sprinkle with sugar while frying.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Crumble bread in milk.
Add ground beef and salt and pepper. Mix up mixture and form into small balls.
Place in a casserole dish.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Combine
first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil
and
vanilla	until creamy.
Stir in potatoes and raisins. Add
dry ingredients, stirring only until moistened. Pour into
2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: no name dessert
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix grated cheese with sausage.
Slowly mix in Bisquick.
Roll into little balls and cook at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes or 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shredded carrot salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill before serving.
If on diet, leave out mayonnaise and sugar.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Cook rice according to package.
In large skillet, put pork steak, thinly sliced with fat removed.
Add crushed garlic and cook until done.
Pour bottle of soy sauce over pork slices and simmer. Cook frozen peas according to package.
Combine rice, pork steak mix, peas and water chestnuts, sliced and drained.
In skillet or large pot, cook on low heat until mixture is hot.
May substitute any ingredients or add anything, like corn or other vegetables. Easily reheated.

title: braised wild duck
directions: Clean ducks well.
Rub ducks well inside and out with salt and tabasco.
Combine other seasonings.
Make one or two incisions in breast of ducks.
Stuff with seasonings.
Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add ducks, cover. Cook at low temperature about 30 minutes.
Add water and cook 2 hours.
Thicken gravy.

title: apple dip
directions: Bring to hard boil for 1 minute.
Cool and serve.

title: super bowl cider
directions: Pour 6 ounces boiling water into mugs.
Add 1 caramel cube. Stir in cider mix.
Top with half whipped cream and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Serves 2.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Mix shortening and sugar.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into pans. Bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serve with apple butter.

title: 7 layered mexican dip
directions: Use a 9-inch pie plate.
Layer in order as listed.
Make early in the day.
Take out 1 hour before serving.
Serve with Fritos or crackers.

title: strawberry pies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients.
Slowly bring to a rolling boil. Remove from heat.
Decap strawberries.
Lay in pie crust and pour glaze over top of pie.
Refrigerate.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix fruit and 1 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Melt butter in baking dish.
While butter is melting, mix batter in separate bowl.
For batter, mix 1 cup sugar, flour and milk.
Mix well.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Spoon fruit mixture over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot with ice cream.

title: california marmalade
directions: Slice rind off fruit thinly, avoiding white pulp.
Pull remaining pulp from around fruit. Slice rind peelings into thin slivers. Chop fruit, discarding seeds. For each cup of mixed fruit, add 3 cups of water.
Let stand overnight.
Place fruit and water in stainless or enamel pan and boil 10 minutes.
Let stand overnight.
Next day, add 1 cup sugar for each cup of fruit.
Boil 45 minutes. Stir in one bottle of Certo (or 2 packs Certo). Remove from heat. Stir and skim for 5 minutes. Bottle and seal with wax.

title: mock orange julius
directions: Combine orange juice concentrate, milk, water, vanilla and Equal in blender.
Blend at high speed.
Add ice cubes and blend until cubes are dissolved.
Makes 4 servings.
Calories per serving:
Diabetic exchanges per serving:
milk 0, vegetable 0, fruit 1, bread 0, meat 0 and fat 0.

title: butter horns
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cool.
Add yeast.
Let dissolve. Add eggs, then flour.
Knead well.
Put in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double.
Divide dough in thirds.
Roll to 9-inch circle.
Brush with butter.
Cut in wedges.
Roll wedges toward center.
Put in greased pan and curve brush with melted butter.
Let rise until very light.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: desire's cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese; beat until smooth.
Add milk and lemon juice.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate until firm.
Top with fruit filling.

title: croatian strudel
directions: Sift flour and salt in bowl.
Moisten with egg, shortening and warm water.
Knead on board for 15 to 20 minutes.
Set aside for half an hour.
Cover table with cloth dust with flour.
Stretch dough until thin.
Add filling, 2 pounds apples, sliced thin. Spread over dough.
Add bread crumbs all over apples, then add sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Dot with butter.
Roll up and bake in 350° oven.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add 1 cup cottage cheese. Beat 2 eggs; add to mixture. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon. Dip in powdered sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: chicken vegetable hot dish
directions: Combine soup, milk, chicken, 1/2 cup cheese and vegetables. Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with remaining cheese and the onion rings.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes until the onion rings are brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Put in casserole or individual shells. Top with corn flakes.
Heat through at 350° about 30 minutes.
Note:
Shrimp and/or crabmeat may be substituted for chicken.

title: layered fruit bars
directions: Prepare desired filling (recipes follows); set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix in flour and salt.
Reserve 1/2 cup mixture.
Press remaining mixture evenly in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Then add pepper, onions, celery and peas.
Spread mayonnaise carefully.
Top with sugar, cheese and bacon.
May also use bacon bits.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Seedless grapes and maraschino cherries may be added if desired.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Place thawed potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together salt, onion, soup and cheese.
Pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes and drizzle butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick elegant chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in pan; do not season.
Pour mixture of other ingredients over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 340°.
Baste.

title: best chocolate cake in the world
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs.
Beat one at a time. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with syrup.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in sheet pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: fruit ball
directions: Cream the cream cheese with other ingredients; mixture will be soupy.
Line container with Saran Wrap.
Put mixture in and freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw a little and roll in chopped nuts.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Pour blueberries into glass Corning Ware.
Pour powdered cake mix on top of blueberries evenly.
Slice pats of butter and distribute evenly on top.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Let cool and serve.
Best with a cold glass of milk.

title: grammie's jello salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill until serving.
For a lighter salad, use low-fat cottage cheese and lite Cool Whip.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Partially thaw raspberries; do not drain.
In blender jar, combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend on high speed until mixture thickens.
Add more water, a little at a time, to reach desired consistency.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Serve immediately.

title: refreshing summer dessert
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Pour into individual glass dessert dishes (sherbets are nice).
When Jell-O has hardened, decorate with grapes, which have been chilled and frosted with sugar.
Garnish with mint leaves.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Layer first five ingredients in bowl.
Top with Cheddar cheese and bacon bits.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and lemon juice.
Shake to dissolve sugar.
Add salt and pepper; shake.
Add milk, mayonnaise and buttermilk; mix thoroughly.
Pour over cabbage and carrot.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: mammy's quick banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Let stand 2 hours, then drain. Combine the next 4 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let set and dissolve.
Put in freezer cartons.
You may freeze them.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix refried beans with taco seasoning. Put in baking dish; smooth sour cream on top and top with grated cheese. Heat in oven at 350° until cheese has melted. Serve hot or keep on warming tray and serve with taco chips.

title: cranberry tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 1 quart.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese stand to room temperature.
Chop beef, olives, mushrooms and onion.
Mix all ingredients together and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: spicy pot roast
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown on all sides.
Combine remaining ingredients and put over meat.
Cover and simmer for 3 hours or until tender, turning occasionally.

title: anise slices(biscotti)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In large bowl, cream butter, sugar and anise.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture and almonds.
Turn out onto a floured surface and knead until smooth.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into a roll about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until firm to the touch (30 to 35 minutes).
Remove and cool slightly.
While still warm, cut rolls into crosswise slices, 1/2-inch thick.
Return to oven and bake until lightly toasted.
Turn to other side and toast lightly.
Cool completely.
Store in a tightly covered tin.

title: three bean bake
directions: Cut up bacon; fry until brown.
In a separate skillet, cook hamburger and onion until just done.
Drain.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Dissolve cubes in boiling water. Add vegetables and cook until tender. Add salt and pepper.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chili
directions: While sirloin and ground beef are cooking, prepare other ingredients.
Add to meat, onion and green peppers and jalapeno. Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste and water.
Mix well.
Add the other ingredients except beans.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.
Add beans; mix well.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese if desired.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix in a pie plate the flour; add on top of flour, sugar, salt, oil and milk.
Pat sides first, then bottom.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes (prick crust) or add filling and bake.

title: grandma's apple goodie
directions: Pare and core apples and slice into a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Crumb mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls in pan and bake as directed.
Let cool and then spread mixture of dressing, mayonnaise and sour cream over top.
Cut into squares.
Distribute vegetables over dressing and sprinkle with cheese.

title: peachy cobbler
directions: Pare and slice the peaches into 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle brown sugar over peaches.
Blend flour, sugar and butter. Top
peaches with this mixture.
Pack down.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until top is golden brown.
Cool. Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: thin crust pizza
directions: Brush the flatbread lightly with olive oil and sprinkle with garlic.
Bake for 7 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and add toppings.
Bake for an additional 15 minutes.
Lo-cal, low-fat healthy!

title: banana cream roll
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat eggs (room temperature) until foamy; add sugar gradually.
Stir in flour, 1/2 cup mashed bananas, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Line jelly roll pan with wax paper and grease.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle towel with confectioners sugar; roll up.
Roll inside it and cool completely.
Unroll; spread with Cool Whip. Place bananas at end of roll; re-roll.

title: corn salad
directions: Slice green onions and their tops.
Stir together green onions, corn, tomatoes, mayonnaise, yogurt, basil, salt and pepper in a large bowl. Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: chocolate tofu nutritional shake
directions: Combine ingredients in blender 1/2 at a time.
Whirl until smooth and creamy.
Serve cold.
Wonderful as a complete protein breakfast drink or for snack anytime.
Any fresh fruit in season such as berries, cantaloupe or papaya can be substituted for the chocolate flavor.
Pour into tall glasses.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: steak and black bean chili
directions: Cut the beef into 1-inch cubes. Place the beef cubes into a slow cooker and turn it on low. Sprinkle the chili powder, garlic powder and cumin over the meat. Peel and chop the onion, adding it to the crock as you chop. Seed and chop the green pepper, adding it to the crock as you chop. Drain and rinse the cans of beans and add them to the slow cooker. Add the tomatoes and the sugar. Cover and cook on low (200°) for 8 to 10 hours. Uncover and stir in the tomato paste. Season with salt and pepper to taste and stir well. Serve at once, garnishing as desired with sour cream and cheese. Makes 8 servings.

title: helen morley's potato doughnuts
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat eggs and sugar together. Add potatoes and lard; beat well.
Alternate additions of milk and flour.
Place into covered bowl.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll out, cut out and deep fry in hot shortening or oil at 365° until golden brown.
Turn over with fork in order to brown both sides.
Fry 2 to 4 at a time.
Drain excess oil by placing doughnuts onto paper towels.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch or flour, jello and water. Cook until thick.
Remove from heat; blend in strawberries.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Pour in pie crust; top with whipped cream.

title: coffee flavored cookies
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar until well mixed. Add the egg and stir.
Mix the coffee powder with the milk until powder dissolved and add to the mixture.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt and add to mixture and stir until smooth.
Roll dough into 1 inch balls. Flatten onto a greased cookie sheet. Bake about 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
Makes 15-20 cookies.

title: cherry cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs; cream together.
Add flour alternately with milk and cherry juice.
Add almond and vanilla extracts.
Fold in cherries last.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or 300° for 2 hours.

title: best potatoes ever
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Peel and shred.
Add chicken soup, butter, onions and sour cream.
Place in Pam sprayed baking pan or dish in layers with shredded cheese between or mix cheese with other ingredients as preferred.
Finish with layer of shredded cheese over the top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Heat milk almost to boiling.
Beat egg yolks and sugar together until frothy and light.
Gradually add hot milk.
Reduce heat.
Crumble crackers into milk (1 package of crackers makes 2 cups).
Stir constantly until mixture boils.
Add coconut and stir until pudding bubbles thickly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Serve warm or cold.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter, eggs and sugar.
Add bananas and vanilla.
Sift together salt, baking soda and flour.

title: sandy's spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: green beans in cream cheese sauce
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Blend cream cheese with milk, salt and celery seed.
Add sauteed onion and heat slowly.
Heat green beans and drain.
Place in serving dish and pour cheese sauce over.
Garnish with French fried onion rings, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: summertime cooler
directions: Blend together and serve chilled.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set good in the middle. Stick a knife in middle to see if it is done; knife will come out clean.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil one medium sized potato until soft; drain off excess water.
With fork or potato masher, start mashing powdered sugar into potato.
One potato will use around one box of powdered sugar, but may use more or less.
Keep adding powdered sugar until it is the consistency of pie dough.
Powder rolling board with powdered sugar.
Roll out potato as for a pie.
Spread peanut butter (creamy or crunchy) over potato and roll as for jelly roll. Cut into slices.
Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Boil the sugar and milk until it forms ball in cold water. Then take off stove.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and salt.
Stir all up until creamy.
Pour in pan; cool and cut.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat corn tortillas for 30 seconds until they are soft. Remove from heat and put 1 tablespoon chopped onion and 1 tablespoon grated cheese inside tortilla.
Roll into an enchilada. Layer in a casserole dish.
Pour 2 cans of chili over the top of the corn tortillas.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbling.

title: lime salad
directions: Stir dry Jell-O into cream cheese. Add boiling water. Cool in refrigerator, then add pineapple and nuts, if desired.
Pour into mold and chill until set.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling salted water 8 to 10 minutes, covered. Drain; set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in heavy saucepan over low heat. Add celery and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add flour, salt, pepper and dry mustard, stirring until blended. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Stir in cheese and carrots.
Pour in casserole dish. Combine bread crumbs and remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle over carrots.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix and garlic; add peppers, onions and chestnuts, then spinach.
Chill and serve.

title: scalloped chicken
directions: Thicken broth of chicken with flour and milk.
Add soup, toast, celery, onions and pimentos together.
Grease pan.
Add half of bread mixture with 1/2 of chicken.
Then add remaining mixture and chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: suis' lemon chess pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add corn meal and lemon juice.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until pie is firm.

title: ma's spice cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Then add alternately the remainder.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes. Recipe may be doubled and use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan. Mix sugar and cinnamon; add to butter. Add orange juice and stir until mixed well. (I usually leave mine on stove until it almost comes to a boil.)

title: hot crab squares
directions: In a medium bowl, combine first 7 ingredients. Cut bread into quarters and spread crab mixture on squares.
Arrange on an ungreased cookie sheet. Broil 4 to 6-inches from heat for 5 minutes or until bubbly hot and golden brown.
Serve immediately.

title: jelly roll
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat yolks well; add the sugar and mix well.
Add the beaten whites until thoroughly mixed.
Fold in lightly sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Pour into a waxed paper lined 14 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan (cookie sheet with sides).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Combine eggs and milk.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring thoroughly.
Place in greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full. Cream together remaining ingredients.
Drop cream cheese mixture in center of cake mix.
Cover with remaining cake mix.
Bake according to cake mix directions.

title: fried indian bread
directions: Mix well.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Roll out thin.
Cut in squares.
Fry in hot oil.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: In hot skillet, cook meat and onions until meat is done. Drain off grease.
Combine soups, chilies and sauce together.
Mix with meat and onions.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Cut each tortilla into 4 pieces.
Place a layer of tortillas in bottom of casserole dish. Then add a layer of meat mixture, cheese, then tortillas and continue until meat mixture is gone.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Pare potatoes and place in cold water before grating.
Mix and blend well the grated potatoes, egg yolks, salt, pepper, flour and grated onions.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Place 1-inch of oil or shortening in skillet and heat.
Drop batter from spoon into hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Turn only once. Pancakes are best when eaten immediately.
Serve with sour cream or applesauce.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add pepper, onions and celery.
Brown with meat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve on long, thin spaghetti.
Can freeze.

title: grandma's red cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients and cover pan tightly; steam until cabbage is tender, approximately 30 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs in a bowl.
Heat 1-inch of oil in skillet or saucepan over medium-high heat.
Pour batter into funnel, holding finger over end.
Drizzle in spiral shape into oil.
Cook until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Coat with confectioners sugar.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Place pie filling in graham cracker crust. Combine cream cheese with cool whip and spread over pie filling. Chill at least one hour before serving.

title: ecuadorian shrimp seviche
directions: * Preferable with heads; remove the heads when they are cooked and you are peeling them.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk and vanilla. Add lemon juice and beat again. Pour into pie crust and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: hot muffin appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread mixture on English muffins. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Cut muffins into quarters.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple pies(makes 2)
directions: Stir first 3 ingredients together.
Pour into pie crusts.
Top with Cool Whip (makes 2).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and debone.
Mix both cans of soup and 1/2 stick of butter.
Heat until butter is melted.
Pour soup and butter mix over chicken.
Then take stuffing mix and pour over the top of that.
Make sure that it is even and smooth.
Then take cup of chicken broth and pour over that.
Dot the top with the rest of the butter. Bake at 375° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese and spinach bake
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix together with all other ingredients, except 1/4 cup cheese.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour (sifted with salt) alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavorings, beating well. Pour into a 10-inch greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
May be frosted with your favorite frosting or glaze or served plain.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and 1 cup sugar.
Add eggs; beat until fluffy. Add vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan. Peel and slice apple.
Arrange slices in batter.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together and put in 8-inch round quiche dish at 350° for 20 minutes.
Make ahead of time, say 2 hours or so.

title: filling for white cake
directions: Mix and cook until thick (looks transparent).
Cool slightly and spread between layers of cake.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Brown meat, mushrooms and onions in butter until onions are done.
Add soup, water, seed and seasoning.
Stir, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring frequently.
Just prior to serving over noodles, blend in sour cream.

title: jade salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar.
Add cottage cheese and mayonnaise (blended).
Mix well. Chill until it starts to congeal.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and put in greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tuna roll
directions: Prepare dough using mix and 2/3 cup milk.
Roll dough into 18 x 10-inch rectangle or line pie plate with 2/3 of the dough and use the rest for a top.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine onion, tuna and dill weed with 1/2 cup of mushroom soup, reserving the rest. Spread mixture over dough and roll up.
Seal edges tightly by pinching sides together.
Bake with sealed edges down.
Cut slits on top and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.
Mix reserved soup and 1/4 cup of milk.
Pour over top.
May add slices of cheese before pouring soup.

title: deviled chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces on 2 shallow, foil-lined baking pans. Make deviled sauce by combining ketchup, mustard, horseradish, Worcestershire sauce and garlic.
Brush over chicken generously. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Brush again with sauce, bake 15 minutes.
Turn chicken once more.
Brush with sauce.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Serve with parslied potatoes and boiled carrots.
Yields 20 servings.

title: layered jello
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan. Grease lightly with salad oil.

title: raw apple pie
directions: Mix together well and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then lower heat to 350° until firm.

title: banana strawberry punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in 4 or 5 containers.
When taken out of freezer to thaw, pour about 3 cups of 7-Up or ginger ale over each container and let thaw.
Very good.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken breast until tender.

Remove from broth (save the broth), debone the chicken, and cut into bite size pieces. Return the chicken to the pot, cover with the saved broth, add 1 cup of milk, margarine and salt and pepper to satisfy your taste. Bring mixture to a boil.
Flatten the biscuits as thin as possible.
Cut into narrow strips and add one at a time to boiling mixture.
Reduce heat to a slow boil and continue to cook until biscuit strips are thoroughly cooked.
You may need to add more milk until you reach the texture that is your satisfaction.
Stir constantly to prevent sticking.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Blend cream cheese in with potatoes until melted.
Add diced onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Add egg and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain well.
Melt very slowly. Mix melted margarine and cheese with broccoli.
Melt remaining margarine and pour over crushed crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Mix eggs and milk together; beat.
Place cubed bread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Add sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over bread, meat and cheese (knife through a little).
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt butter and add cocoa.
Cream sugar and eggs.
Add to butter and cocoa.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Mix well. pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350°. While cake is still hot, spread Marshmallow Creme on top.

title: easy potatoes au gratin
directions: In a 9 x 9-inch baking pan, combine potatoes and celery. Blend soup undiluted with mustard; pour over vegetables.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Wash, peel and dice potatoes, onion and celery.
Add just enough water to cover vegetables.
Cook until they're barely soft enough to pierce with a fork.

title: doritos mexican
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Crush Doritos in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add meat and onion.
Pour tomatoes and soup over. Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: 15 minute meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients except 1/2 of the tomato paste and pack into muffin pan.
Cover with rest of tomato paste.
You may add grated cheese on top (optional).
Bake for 15 minutes in 425° oven. Enjoy.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove bowl from mixer; stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch pans or one 9 x13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.

title: calico beans
directions: Drain all cans of beans.
Mix ingredients together well.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: bacon appetizer crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat cream cheese, bacon, cheese, onion, parsley and milk in small mixing bowl.
Cut crescents in half crosswise to form 2 triangles out of each one.
Spread mixture on flat surface and roll one corner over.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: cappuccino parfaits
directions: Dissolve coffee in hot water in medium bowl. Add milk, pudding mix and cinnamon. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes or until thickened.

Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon half of the pudding mixture into 5 dessert dishes. Sprinkle with crushed cookies. Spoon remaining pudding mixture over crushed cookies. Garnish each serving with an additional 1 tablespoon lite whipped topping, if desired. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 5 servings.

title: fast and fit potato chowder
directions: In microwave, melt butter in 2 1/2 to 3-quart microwave-safe dish on High, 1 minute.
Add leeks and bell peppers; microwave on High 3 minutes.
Stir in potatoes, broth, thyme and bay leaves; cover and cook on High 20 minutes.
Remove and discard bay leaves. Remove 4 cups cooked potatoes with a slotted spoon and put into electric blender.
Add milk and puree until smooth.
Return mixture to dish.
Stir in corn, parsley and cayenne.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat on High 3 minutes.

title: the best brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl. Pour into 9 X 13 pan and bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: perfection salad
directions: In saucepan, soften the gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add sweetener, salt and 1 cup of water.
Stir over low heat to dissolve gelatin.
Add 2 cups of water, vinegar and lemon juice. Chill until mixture is partially set.
Stir in the cabbage, celery, green pepper and pimiento.
Pour into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf dish.
Chill until firm.

title: wild rice
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until rice is well coated.
Heat sherry and chicken stock to boil.
Stir in rice and pour into baking dish.
Cover and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° until liquids are absorbed by rice.

title: double glazed rum cake
directions: Preheat oven
to
Grease
and flour a Bundt pan. In a large bowl, stir cake mix, pudding, eggs, water, rum and oil until smooth.
Pour
into
prepared
pan and bake 1 hour. Cool in
pan 25
minutes.
Invert
onto serving plate.
Prick top.
Spoon and brush Rum Glaze evenly over cake, allowing the cake to
absorb the
glaze.
When
cake is completely cooled, drizzle with Chocolate Glaze and sprinkle with walnuts.

title: grandma's gingerbread cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix flour, soda, salt and spices.
Heat shortening in saucepan until melted.
Cool slightly.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs; mix well.
Add 4 cups flour.
Mix well.
Turn mixture into lightly floured surface.
Add flour to make firm dough.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut cookies in holiday shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: betty crocker brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Make brownie mix as on package except bake 20 minutes.
Mix together other ingredients.
Pour over brownies. Bake until topping is set, 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with pie filling.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Soften butter and blend in the sugar, then the beaten egg. Combine flour, salt and vanilla, then add it to the butter mixture.
Combine thoroughly and chill dough in a ball for 3 to 4 hours.
Roll chilled dough out to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cutters.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes, watching carefully.
The cookies have tanned slightly when done.

title: chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine the ingredients, except shoestring potatoes.
Just before serving, add the shoestring potatoes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Saute veggies in butter until tender-crisp.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine soup and sour cream and mix with stuffing mix and vegetables.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for about 35 min., remove foil cover to crisp top, if desired.
Omit sour cream and it still tastes good.
Also add chopped green pepper, fresh peas, etc.

title: tofu egg salad sandwich
directions: Crumble tofu into small pieces with a fork.
Combine with tahini, pickle, onion, mustard, oil, turmeric, basil and celery seed.
Divide filling in half.
Makes 2 sandwiches.

title: zucchini medley
directions: In 2-quart casserole combine all ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Cover with lid and cook on Medium in microwave, removing and stirring twice.
Let stand 5 minutes, covered.
Top with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: cottage cheese dip
directions: Blend all in blender or food processor.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.

title: spinach spread
directions: Squeeze all water from spinach.
Combine with other ingredients and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Better if made a day ahead.
Serve with rye bread.
This spread works well as a dip in a hollowed out bread round or as a stuffing for raw mushroom caps.

title: kiwi jam
directions: Peel and cut fruit.
Cook and mash.
Add other ingredients. Mix well.
Boil 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour into jelly glasses or pint jars.
Seal with paraffin and cover.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain.
Mix soup with milk; stir constantly while heating.
Don't boil.
Add broccoli, pepper to taste, butter and herb.
Heat and serve.

title: finger sandwiches
directions: Mix cream cheese and onion, finely grated.
Cut edges off bread.
Spread cream cheese mixture in middle of bread slices. Top with pickle.
Roll and then pinch edges.
Chill overnight. Slice.

title: terry's spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onion, bell pepper and celery into small chunks.
Place in large pan with ground sirloin and brown well.
Drain any excess grease from pan.
Drain mushrooms and add to meat mixture.
Add margarine, Accent, garlic, sugar, salt, pepper, oregano and Worcestershire sauce.
Brown well.
Add soup mix; blend.
Drain tomatoes and cut into chunks.
Add catsup, tomato sauce and tomatoes to meat mixture.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Serve over favorite pasta.

title: cheese and vegetable chowder
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart pan, cook vegetables, covered and stirring occasionally, 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour.
Mix well.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add chicken broth to vegetable mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring well.
Gradually add cheese.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until cheese has melted.
Gradually add milk. Season with salt and pepper.
Bring just to a boil, but do not boil.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve with croutons.

title: stuffed shells
directions: First boil the shells until soft, then cool.
As the shells are cooling, mix in a bowl cheeses and spices, and then take a sheet tray and spread some of the sauce on the bottom of pan.
Stuff the cheese mix in the shells.
Lay them out in the sheet tray and then cover with sauce and Mozzarella cheese on the top of the shells and bake in oven at 350° for twenty minutes or until all cheese is melted.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, garlic powder, soda, cheese and milk (or buttermilk) together; beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop by spoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°. Melt 1/2 stick of oleo or butter and brush the biscuits while they are hot.

title: jazz up broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook until bubbly.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in onion, mayonnaise and eggs.
Carefully mix in broccoli.
Turn into a 2-quart greased casserole and place uncovered into a pan of hot water.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top will be nicely browned.

title: peach crunch
directions: Pour peaches in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over top.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Top with pecans and coconut. Bake for 55 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm.

title: spaghetti squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Toss spaghetti, eggs, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Spread in pan.
Spoon sauce over.
Place sliced pepperoni over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° until pick comes out clean.

title: avocado dip
directions: In medium bowl, with mixer at low speed, gradually beat cream of chicken soup into cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in garlic and chili powder.
Mash avocado.
Beat into soup mixture.
Top with shallots and serve with bagels or tortilla chips.

title: strul
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add milk and flour alternately, last portion of milk last.
If it is too stiff, thin with cream.
Drop by teaspoon on hot iron.
When baked, place roller on top of rack and roll up in rolls.

title: party pizza
directions: Mix all.
Put on slice of party rye bread; bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: lick-the-dasher-ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, and salt in top of double boiler. Blend in milk gradually and cook over hot water, stirring occasionally until mixture is thickened, about 12 or 15 minutes. Blend a small amount of the hot mixture into the eggs, then stir the eggs into the rest of the mixture. Cook
4 or 5 minutes more, stirring constantly. Chill custard. Add vanilla and chilled cream. Fill gallon freezer not more than 2/3 full. Follow manufacturers directions for your ice cream freezer.

title: gwen's garden salad
directions: Mix the corn, peas and green beans all together and then add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together and set overnight in refrigerator.

title: rice and spinach soup
directions: Chop spinach.
Heat oil and butter in a 6-quart soup kettle. Add garlic and onions; saute until softened, about 5 minutes.
Add chopped spinach and saute 3 additional minutes.
Add rice and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Ladle soup into warm bowls and sprinkle with pepper and cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: caramel sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, cream, corn syrup and butter.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Thin with a little cream, if necessary.
Delicious with apples as a dip!

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, bread crumbs and sugar.
Put firmly on bottom of buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: vinegar and oil salad dressing
directions: Mix in blender, pouring oil in last and very slowly.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Cook bacon strips in broiler pan until about brown.
Add cabbage, onion, bell pepper, tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Add vinegar.
Cook on low heat for 45 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat
eggs;
add sugar, flour, vanilla and cream.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas; pour egg mixture
over
the
layers.
Crumble a few wafers on top.
This is an original recipe!

title: mom's carrot tacos
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet; drain grease.
Add onion and tomato sauce.
Cook until onion is done.
Cook carrots and potatoes in a medium saucepan until done.
Drain and mash the carrots and potatoes; add to ground beef mixture.
Stir.
Serve on tortillas with lettuce, garlic salt and hot sauce.
Serves about 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Cook soups, onion and cheese.
Add broccoli to soup mixture, then add rice.
Put in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagne rolls
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Rinse under cold water and drain again.
Set aside.
Squeeze out as much moisture from spinach as possible.
Stir together spinach, 3/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese, Ricotta cheese, nutmeg, salt and pepper.

title: joe froggers(a molasses cookie)
directions: Mix the shortening together with the sugar and cream thoroughly.
Stir in the salt, molasses, water and rum.
Add baking soda and spices to the flour and add to the creamed mixture.
Mix well until dough forms.
Chill dough thoroughly. Roll out on a lightly floured board and cut into large 3-inch circles 1/8-inch thick.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and sprinkle tops with granulated sugar.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator bread pudding
directions: Combine water, sugar, bread, milk, salt, gelatin and vanilla in blender.
Pour mixture into saucepan and simmer slowly until smooth.
Cool.
Return mixture to blender.
Add buttermilk and cinnamon; blend until smooth.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serves 1.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine ingredients with mixer.
Place dropfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Careful, they burn easily!

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Blend in egg and flavorings.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Roll out to 3/16-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 to 5 dozen.

title: coconut blondies(low calorie - 90 calories each)
directions: Melt oleo in medium saucepan over medium heat.
Add cereal. Cook 2 minutes, stir constantly.
Remove from heat; add brown sugar, vanilla and egg, stirring well.
Set aside cereal mixture. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to cereal, stirring well. Spread into 8-inch square pan, coated with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool and cut into 2-inch square bars.
Store in covered container in fridge.
Yields 16 bars.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Let stand 2 hours or better to marinate salad dressing into pasta.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix and put on English muffins or crackers in broiler.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and sugar (1 cup) together; fold into Cool Whip.
Spread onto cooled crust.
Add 2 cups boiling water to jello; stir to dissolve.
Add frozen strawberries.
Break strawberries up into the jello.
Let it gel for 10 minutes, then spread over the top of cream cheese filling.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice with water and salt.
Add other ingredients with cheese and butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: end of the garden
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Be sure meal covers all ingredients well. Place ingredients in large 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Bake in oven until veggies are brown and tender. Bake at 350°.

title: aunt amy's cookies
directions: Mix and sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg.
Add flour and remaining ingredients.
Arrange by 1/2 teaspoonful on buttered cookie sheet.
Flatten with a knife or spatula, dipping in water. Bake at 350° until delicate brown (8 to 10 minutes).
Remove from cookie sheet while warm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs, sugar and zucchini together. Add 2 cups sifted flour, soda, salt and cinnamon to zucchini mixture, mixing well. Add vanilla and nuts. Makes 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour and salt with mixer and add to scalded milk in double boiler.
Cook until creamy texture.
Remove from heat and add Pet milk.
Let cool.
(Best to refrigerate overnight.)
Add pint of cream and vanilla just before freezing. Makes 1 gallon.

title: strawberry seafoam mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Put cream cheese in hot gelatin.
Break cream cheese up.
Let stand for a few minutes. Beat with wire whip until cream cheese dissolves.
Add frozen strawberries (juice and all).
Stir until well mixed in gelatin. Add whipped topping.
Beat with wire whip until thoroughly mixed and thickened.
Pour into pan.
Chill until firm.
Serves 10.

title: romana's amaretti
directions: You will need an icing bag.
Grate the almond paste in a bowl. Beat the egg whites, then mix with the grated almond paste.
Mix well with a wooden spoon.
Fill the icing bag, then squeeze out bottom, forming macaroons.
Place in neat rows in a cookie sheet lined with foil.
Top with cherry on each cookie.

title: hot shrimp appetizer
directions: Saute butter, onion and green peppers.
Add tomatoes, crackers, salt, pepper, hot sauce, nutmeg and thyme.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add 2 small cans of shrimp.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs and Bisquick until smooth.
Pour over meat.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°. Top with tomatoes and cheese.
Return to oven for an additional 5 to 8 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according	to directions; drain well.
Mix with other ingredients.	Bake
at
350°	for
30 minutes until hot.
If you double the recipe, do not double water chestnuts. Serves 6 to 8.

title: caesar salad
directions: In large salad bowl, mix garlic, salt, pepper, anchovies, lemon juice and egg.
Add olive oil and mix to combine.
Add lettuce and toss.
Then add Parmesan cheese and croutons.
Serves 4.

title: deano's delicious spaghetti sauce
directions: Put
tomato
sauce and tomato paste in large pan. Start cooking
at
medium
heat.	Chop tomatoes and add with oregano and celery salt, after sauce starts to simmer.	Start hamburger
and sausage cooking in skillet.
Dice onion very small and saute
in with
salt	and pepper. After hamburger and sausage have browned, drain in
colander.
Add
to
sauce after having cooked approximately 1 hour.
Add 2 bay leaves and keep on low heat for 6 hours,
stirring
occasionally.
Add
chili powder approximately 1 hour
before serving. Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: lemony refrigerator cheesecake
directions: In a bowl, mix crumbs and butter.
Press into the bottom and 2-inches up the sides of a greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Chill.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, water and cornstarch..
Cook mixture until thick. Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Pat strawberries into pie shells. Add the mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: beau monde dip(for fresh vegetables)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
(Beau Monde seasoning made by Spice Islands.)

title: chocolate eclairs
directions: For chocolate sauce, mix sugar, 1/4 c. milk, cocoa and butter together in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts, then tear chicken into pieces.
Put in a baking pan and add both cans of soup.
Let bake for 15 minutes, then follow directions on Stove Top stuffing box.
Spread over chicken and soup.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: bistro chicken salad
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat chicken, bouillon, cloves and 3 cups of water to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from liquid; set aside to cool.
