When chicken is cooled, discard skin and bones; tear meat into bite size pieces.
Trim stems from green beans; cut 1/4-inch slices.
In 2 inches of water, boil in a 2-quart saucepan over high heat; heat beans to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 3 minutes.
Cook potatoes until fork-tender.
Add all ingredients together and chill.

title: french cream frosting
directions: Cream the margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add flour, one spoon at a time.
Slowly add the warm milk.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; bring to boil.
Add cream cheese and beat until dissolved.
Cool.

title: asparagus canapes
directions: Trim crusts from bread slices and discard.
With rolling pin, roll slices thin.
Spread with softened Blue cheese and cream cheese mixture.
Place 1 asparagus spear on top and roll up.
Cut in half.
Melt butter and grated cheese and then blend.
Dip rolls into butter.
Chill or freeze.
When ready to serve, place rolls on a cookie sheet.
Heat at 350° until bubbly (approximately 10 minutes).
If frozen, bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: one-dish meal
directions: Put the cut up chicken in a pan.
Put potatoes around chicken. Add the soup and milk on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook sliced apples until thick.
Place in an unbaked pie shell.
Lay another pie shell on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: deer jerky
directions: Cut meat into thin slices.
Combine ingredients.
Soak meat in the sauce for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Put in oven at 150° for 12 hours.
Turn every 6 hours.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Bring to a full boil.
Cool to a lukewarm.
Add 3 cups flour.
Beat well.
Beat in yeast and eggs.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let stand until double (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Turn out on lightly floured surface and cut to desired shape.
Cover and let rise.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: never fail frosting
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Stir into egg whites that have been beaten stiff.
Add shortening, powdered sugar and flavoring.
Beat with electric mixer until light and fluffy.

title: twyla's berry cake
directions: This does not raise high, more like bars.

title: angel dessert
directions: Break cake into bite-sized pieces in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with half of the undrained pineapple and the cherries. Spread half of whipped topping over all and sprinkle with half of coconut.
Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sharon's company sausage
directions: Cut crust
off
bread;
butter and place in 9 x 13-inch dish. Brown sausage.
Sprinkle over bread. Mix milk and eggs; pour
over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake
at
350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix chopped nuts, raisins, pitted prunes, dates, hot water, and soda together. Let stand while you mix in another bowl the following: mayonnaise, sifted flour, cocoa, and vanilla. Mix all together and bake in greased cake pan or loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until done.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Cook
macaroni
according
to
package
instructions. Season with salt, pepper
and
cup
shredded
cheese; set aside. Saute onion and
pepper
in margarine; add the seafood and cook for 2 to
3 minutes.
Set aside.
Crumble sausage and fry until done; set aside.
Mix Worcestershire sauce, mushroom soup, milk, mayonnaise
and
remaining
cheese.
Combine
this mixture with macaroni
mixture,
seafood
mixture and sausage. Mix well.
Turn into a
greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake
in a 350° oven about 25 to 30 minutes, until bubbly hot.

title: mrs. snap's cookies
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter, cereal and sugar together.
Chill. Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate mixture in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate and place on wax paper until chocolate sets.

title: creme brulee
directions: Beat egg yolks until very thick.
Gradually add 1/3 cup sugar. Scald whipping cream in top of double boiler over direct heat. Pour scalded cream gradually into egg mixture.
Return to double boiler and cook over hot water, stirring frequently until thickened, 5 minutes.
Pour into heatproof dish.
Cool.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar.
Place under broiler until sugar melts and forms a glaze.
Chill.
Serve with fresh berries.

title: berry ice cream
directions: In blender, puree 12 ounces tofu with vanilla, honey and salt for 1 minute.
Transfer to covered container and put in freezer overnight.
The next day, puree the rest of the tofu (6 ounces), then add berries or frozen juice and blend together with the frozen tofu.

title: chili
directions: Cook onions and garlic until onion is clear.
Add beef and crumble up.
Brown all together.
Add all remaining ingredients. Simmer 45 minutes.
May be garnished with melted Cheddar cheese.

title: ann's taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef. Put all ingredients in a pot and simmer for about 1/2 hour to 45 minutes. Serve with corn bread, Doritos, tortilla chips, Fritos, etc.

title: snickerdoodles(soft)
directions: Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture. Chill dough.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll each ball in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 inches apart.
Decorate with bits of candied cherries.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.

title: rice chex dessert
directions: Mix all the above ingredients, except ice cream.
Place 1/2 mixture in pan.
Scoop on softened ice cream.
Top with remaining Rice Chex mixture.

title: loin of pork in red wine
directions: Bake at 350° until done, about 2 hours, turning twice.
Add 1 cup canned beef consomme and bake 20 minutes longer.
Place loin on hot platter; scrape all wine and meat drippings into the sauce and serve, separately with the pork.
Glazed onions and oven-browned new potatoes go well with it.

title: mother's beans
directions: Place beans in baking dish; put bacon on top of beans, then catsup and lastly the brown sugar.
Don't stir!
Cook 2 hours at 325°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Mix all together in a large casserole dish.
Top with cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° about 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Layer all ingredients, then cover with tomatoes.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 350° for thirty minutes.

title: "lift me up" torte - tiramiso
directions: Combine mascarpone cheese, 1/2 cup powdered sugar, 3 tablespoons Kahlua, 2 ounces grated chocolate, 1 teaspoon vanilla and salt; stir well with a wire whisk.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Add taco seasoning with a little water.
Add refried beans, mix well.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread a layer of sour cream over top and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas cinnamon rolls
directions: Unroll dough into 4 rectangles.
(Do not tear apart as in making crescent rolls.)
Butter each rectangle generously. Sprinkle on lots of sugar.
Shake cinnamon on top.
Add pecans. Roll into small logs.
Refrigerate for 3 minutes.
Take out and slice into 1/4 inch thick pinwheels.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet, tucking pinwheel end under roll to prevent unraveling while baking.
Bake according to package instructions.
Remove from oven and glaze.
Make any powdered sugar glaze to spoon on top while rolls are still warm.
Serves 6.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place meat in stove top pan. Cover with water. Add bay leaf and pepper. Cover tightly. Simmer 3 -31/2 hours. Skim fat. Add onion, potato, carrots and caraway. Simmer 20 minutes more. Add cabbage. Simmer 15 minutes. Remove vegetables to warm plate. Glaze with butter. Slice meat and serve.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Use a 15 x 10 x 1-inch well-greased and floured pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Follow cake mix directions except use reserved pineapple juice for liquid.
Add water to measure correctly.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, instant pudding and cold milk.
Fold in drained pineapple and spread over cake. Cover pudding mix with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut and chopped nuts, if desired.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: fried cabbage and noodles
directions: In a large skillet, fry chopped or shredded cabbage in 1/2 cup butter until well done.
Boil noodles in water.
Add a little salt to keep noodles from sticking together.
Boil until well done; drain noodles well.
Mix noodles into cabbage; mix well.
Serve hot.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Blend ingredients in blender until smooth.
Makes equivalent of 1 can Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk.

title: easy chicken-n-rice
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Grease slow cooker and spoon 1/2 mixture into slow cooker.
Place chicken breasts over mixture.
Spoon remaining mixture over chicken.
Cook on medium setting for 4 to 5 hours.

title: fluffy pancake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt 1/3 cup butter in oven at 400°. While butter is melting, whip together all remaining ingredients until frothy.
Pour into baking dish and bake 25 minutes.
Serve with syrup.
Serves 4 to 5 adults.

title: mandu(korean dumplings)
directions: Squeeze water out of spinach.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Lay out the wonton wrappers on a tray.
Take a small bowl of water. Put a spoonful of spinach mixture at the center of each wrapper. Dip finger in water and pass through 2 edges of wrapper over spinach mixture to form a triangle.
Pinch sides to make a triangle.
Steam for 8 to 10 minutes on a pan sprayed with nonstick cooking oil over a pot of boiling water.
Cover.
You can use a double boiler also.

title: derek's pop-pop's chili
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper in skillet until medium-well done.
Add salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce; cover and simmer on low for 1 hour.
Add kidney beans and simmer for 15 more minutes.

title: "hot" pot roast
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Sprinkle garlic powder and meat tenderizer on roast.
Pour in enough water to cover roast about 1/2 inch.
Cook on high for 4 hours.
Add potatoes.
Cook on high for 2 more hours.
Add hot peppers and kraut.
Cook on high for 1 more hour.
Serve.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and 1 cup sugar.
Add other cup of sugar and cream, then add eggs one at a time.
Add flour that has been sifted 5 times.
Add vanillas and salt.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding cornbread mix last.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or skillet.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with lettuce.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar to your mayonnaise.
Mix well together.
Leave your cheese, bacon and dressing for the last three ingredients.
After you have all your ingredients layered, then put your dressing on, then your cheese and last, the bacon.

title: cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 370°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar gradually; beat well.
Fold in chips.
Drop on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper.
Place in oven.
Turn oven off.
Leave in oven until cool.

title: taco lasagne
directions: Brown beef, onion, cumin and garlic.
Stir in chili powder, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pour 1/2 cup taco sauce in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place 5 tortillas on sauce overlapping.
Layer ingredients as follows:
1/2 cup taco sauce, all of meat mixture, sour cream, cheese (reserve some for topping). Top with remaining tortillas, then 1/2 cup sauce.
Bake covered in 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered 5 to 8 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. May be assembled and refrigerated a day ahead.

title: warmed cranberry brie
directions: Peel off top rind of cheese, leaving 1/4-inch rim. Top with cranberry mixture and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons chopped pecans. Bake at 500° for 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Add vegetables to macaroni; salt and pepper to taste.
Add salad dressing as much as desired.
Stir and cool before serving. Will keep several days, if made in advance.

title: zippy eggnog-mix
directions: Combine ingredients; store in airtight container.

title: meringue-nut pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir well. Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed of an electric mixer until foamy. Add sugar; beat until stiff peaks form and sugar dissolves.
Add vanilla; fold in cracker mixture. Spread in a 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 250° for 40 minutes; cool.

title: my shrimp salad
directions: Drain shrimp; cook macaroni.
Chop onion and celery; slice olives and shred cheese.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add Miracle Whip to coat well.
Refrigerate.
Top with additional sliced olives and paprika for garnish.

title: cajun rice and beans
directions: Cook rice and beans according to package directions.
Pour into crock-pot and add sausage and tomato sauce.
Turn to low to keep warm.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Combine in narrow bowl.
Blend on high speed 4 to 6 minutes. Frost cool cake.
Store frosted cake in refrigerator.
Will keep for several days.

title: ensalada de legumbres
directions: Saute sausage in a skillet until light brown. Drain on a paper towel.
Cool.
Crumble.
Place in a large bowl with corn, green beans, sliced tomatoes, parsley, scallions and lettuce. Refrigerate until serving time.
In a small bowl, beat together olive oil, vinegar, salt, pepper and garlic.
Just before serving, pour over salad and toss well.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda, and salt in a bowl; beat.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Scrape the green peeling off the zucchini. Cut the zucchini in half length wise and dig out seeds and soft insides.

title: quick apple salad
directions: Mix together Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Mix in dry, powdered Jell-O.
Toss apples with Cool Whip mixture. Add nuts and salt. Chill and serve.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in large fry pan, saute onions over medium heat until clear.
Reserve 3 tablespoons of cracker crumbs for topping. Place remaining crumbs in the bottom of lightly greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Remove onions from pan with a slotted spoon.
Add soup and onions in alternate layers until full.
Top with cheese and remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: company omelet
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cool.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs. Add milk, mustard, mushrooms, onions and cheese.
Add cooked sausage.
Cut crusts off bread and cut into pieces.
Add crusts to the egg mixture; mix well.
Put into a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until firm and brown around the edges, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple of your pie
directions: Crust: Combine flour, 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1/2 teaspoon of salt. "Cut in" the cold butter and shortening. Chill the contents for 10 to 15 minutes. Whisk together egg and water, then sprinkle over contents 3 tablespoons at a time. Make a ball with the dough. Cut it in half. Flatten each of the halves and wrap in plastic wrap. Put in refrigerator.

title: bisquick "crab" quiche
directions: Lightly oil six ovenproof shells or individual shallow baking dishes.
Set in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
In a small bowl, mix butter or margarine with 1/2 cup of the bread crumbs; set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix remaining 1 cup crumbs, mayonnaise, celery, cheese, sherry, parsley, garlic, paprika and pepper until well blended.

title: macadamia and white chocolate cookies
directions: Mix the flour, soda and salt in a bowl.
Set aside.
Mix the brown sugar and white sugar.
Mix in the butter.
Mix in the eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients alternately with the vanilla chips and nuts.
Do not overmix.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes until light golden brown.
As good as Mrs. Fields.

title: dill bread
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour, sugar, salt, onion, baking soda, dill and yeast.
Add margarine and hot tap water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add cottage cheese, egg and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover bowl and let rise until double in size (about 1 1/2 hours).
Stir mix down.
Turn into a greased loaf pan.
Cover and let rise until double in size (50 minutes).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: beef brisket on the grill
directions: Mix orange juice, beer and Italian dressing.
Pour over meat. Cover and marinate for 2 days.
Add barbecue sauce to marinade and brush on meat.
Seal in foil and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn and cook for 1 1/2 hours more.
Remove from foil and continue to cook until slightly crusty.

title: easy vegetable pie
directions: Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Mix with onion, pepper and cheese in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth and pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes, at 400°.
The Bisquick forms a crust.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites slowly, add sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Place on cookie sheet by teaspoonfuls.
Put cookies in oven, turn oven off. Let set overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper. Add salt, pepper and chili powder. Add corn and tomato. Simmer for 1 hour. Add zucchini and garlic. Simmer until zucchini is soft. Serves 4.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Stir soup until smooth; blend in catsup, oregano and garlic powder.
Heat, stirring frequently.
Spear toast squares and dunk. Yield:
1 1/2 cups.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Make sure mixture is moist.
Shape into small individual loaves and brown in 375° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Pour broth from pan into saucepan and add chopped onions, plus beef stock, making a gravy.
Pour over loaves.
Return to oven at 250° and bake for 1 hour.

title: chocolate mint thins
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa powder, baking soda and salt onto a sheet of wax paper.
Beat sugar and butter until well blended at high speed.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
Reduce speed to low. Gradually beat in sifted mixture until well blended. Refrigerate dough for 30 minutes if it is very soft.

title: hash browns
directions: Layer first 7 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add seasoning as desired.
Combine melted butter with corn flakes and spread on top.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 300°.

title: leg of lamb in marinade
directions: Have your butcher debone the lamb, or do it yourself.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large soup pot fill approximately 1/2 full of water. Add the first 4 ingredients, bring to a boil. Add okra, cook until almost done, add tomatoes and Knorr's seasoning. Turn heat to low and simmer. Season to taste, adding more Knorr's until broth is rich in flavor. Serve with hot cornbread.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Blend sugar and cream cheese.
Add pecans, cherries and pineapple.
Mix well and fold in topping.
Freeze.
Serves 10.

title: monkey bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 12 - cup tube pan. Mix the sugar and cinnamon in a gallon plastic bag.
Working with one can at a time, quarter each biscuit. Coat with the butter, shake in sugar and cinnamon to coat and then gently press into the prepared pan.
Bake 45 - 50 minutes or until browned and pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from the oven and invert.

title: butterscotch "haystacks"
directions: Melt chips. Pour in noodles and nuts. Drop onto wax paper covered cookie sheet (about 1 heaping teaspoonful size). Cool on cookie sheet.

title: lime jello
directions: Pour into dish and refrigerate overnight or 24 hours.

title: peach dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix margarine, flour and pecans.
Press in pie pan and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain and cool.
Slice onion and green pepper; mix with carrots.
Mix all other ingredients in a bowl.
Pour over carrot mix and mix well.
Cover and let stand 12 hours or more before serving.
Will keep in the refrigerator for 2 weeks or more.

title: boston wings
directions: Marinate wings in sauce for 24 hours in refrigerator before cooking.
Simmer wings in covered dish on low in oven until done.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In large skillet saute onion and pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, olives, mushrooms, oregano, garlic powder and ground beef.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Place 1/2 of spaghetti in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of vegetable mix and 1 cup of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix soup and water; pour on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown.

title: not-so-sweet pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add milk, flour and vanilla.
Beat eggs separately. Add to mixture and beat well.
Add nuts and pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans; add onion and pepper.
Marinate overnight in marinade mixture.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange sweet potatoes in an uncovered baking dish. Boil together for 5 minutes. Pour over potatoes. Bake in a 375° oven for 45 minutes, basting occasionally. Serves six.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and jelly.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add 1/2 cup flour and spices.
Dredge chopped fruit in 1/2 cup flour and add remaining flour to mixture.
Add wine to batter. Gradually add soda to buttermilk, then add both to batter.
Add fruit to batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased pan.
Cook at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb crumb
directions: Sprinkle over top of rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Parboil cabbage about 5 minutes or until leaves come off easily.
Mix ground beef, rice, onion, eggs, salt and pepper. Roll each cabbage leaf with some of the meat mixture.
May be held together with toothpicks.
Arrange cabbage rolls, seam side down, in a single layer in lightly greased shallow 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake, covered, for 50 minutes and 10 minutes uncovered at 300°.

title: rabbit (domestic), pheasant or chicken
directions: Cut washed rabbit into serving pieces; salt lightly.
Shake pieces in bag containing pancake flour.
Lay in roaster or Dutch oven pan.
Drizzle melted butter over meat; sprinkle generous pinch of thyme and parsley.
Lay on top the onion and celery.
Mix beef consomme and white wine; pour over meat.
Cover.
Cook in hot oven (450°) for 1/2 hour, basting occasionally.
Lower oven to 350° for 1 hour, basting.
Add more liquid if necessary.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat 7-Up in saucepan until boiling.
Remove from heat and stir in Jell-O, stirring until dissolved.
Cool.
In a large bowl, mix cream cheese, undrained pineapple and sour cream.
Combine with Jell-O mixture and pour into 9 x 5-inch pan.
Chill thoroughly.
Line serving platter with lettuce leaves; invert salad onto plate.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: turnip whip
directions: Combine quartered potatoes, turnips and salt.
Cover with water and boil until turnips and potatoes are very tender.
Drain well.
Mash; add cream, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat until fluffy.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses, mixing well.
Add remaining ingredients (except nuts) and mix.
Chill, then shape into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: applesauce raisin cake(fat-free)
directions: In large bowl, combine applesauce, sugar and liquid Butter Buds.
In separate bowl, sift together flour, soda, cloves and cinnamon.
Add to applesauce mixture.
Stir by hand and mix well. Add raisins.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper.
Brown on both sides in hot oil.
Remove chops.
Add onion soup mix and water to pan drippings; bring to a boil.
Place rice and green pepper in a shallow casserole dish.
Top with chops.
Pour soup mixture over chops, cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil and continue cooking for 15 minutes.

title: lemon frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar with lemon juice.
Add salt.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Grease bottom of casserole; spread half of tortillas, half of meat, half of grated cheese, half of olives and half of corn. Pour half of tomato sauce and salsa, that has been mixed.
Layer rest of tortillas, meat, cheese, olives and corn.
Top with sauce. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: ruth's mexican quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: marinated zucchini salad
directions: Place zucchini in a bowl.
Combine vinegar and next 7 ingredients; stir.
Pour over zucchini; toss.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Serve on lettuce.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla flavoring.
Mix well. Stir in grated zucchini.
Stir together and then add to mixture, flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add chopped nuts, raisins and pineapple.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° in two 9 x 5-inch greased and floured loaf pans.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix pineapple and sugar together and boil for 5 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese and chilled milk together.
Add the box of Jell-O to the pineapple mixture, then fold into the cream cheese and milk.
Chill until set.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Saute onions in olive oil in skillet.
Add zucchini, garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
In bowl, mix eggs, cheese, parsley, rice and thyme.
Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Drizzle a little olive oil over top.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: napoleon cremes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook until butter melts.
Stir in egg.
Cook and stir until mixture is thick, about 3 minutes.
Blend in crumbs and coconut.
Press into buttered 9-inch pan.

title: pork chops with spiced apple wedge
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Over medium heat, brown chops on both sides in oil in a large skillet. Remove from heat and arrange pork chops in a shallow 2 quart baking dish. Return skillet to heat and stir in 1/2 cup of juice, stirring to deglaze pan. Stir in raisins and salt and pour over browned chops.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Beat pumpkin, milk, eggs and sugar.
Beat together and pour into well sprayed pan.
Sprinkle on cake mix.
Pour over this, oleo.
Top with nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: old english crumb cake
directions: Mix sugar, spices, flour and shortening together just as you would pie dough, blending with pastry blender or knives until coarse mealy mixture.
Take out 1/2 cup full.
Into the balance add the sour milk and soda and beat very well. Pour this into a square pan and spread over the top the 1/2 cup of crumbs.
You may also add nut meat finely chopped to the top. Bake in moderate oven about 30 minutes. Do not remove from pan, but let stand so the crumb top will be kept intact.
(No eggs used in this recipe.)

title: apricot cream cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed until smooth and fluffy. Add the apricots, nuts and honey. Serve on whole wheat bread.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Melt shortening in large saucepan.
Blend in brown sugar. Cool 10 minutes.
Beat in eggs, one at a time and add vanilla. Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to other mixture and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread evenly in a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lush pudding
directions: Blend margarine and flour and put in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 of the Cool Whip.
Spread over the crust.

title: sweet and sour fish fillets(microwave)
directions: Arrange fillets in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cover with vented plastic wrap; microwave at High 6 to 7 minutes, or until fish flakes easily, rotating dish 1/2 turn after half the cooking time.
Set aside.
In a 1-quart casserole, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, chives and dry mustard.
Stir in pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Microwave at High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until thickened, stirring once or twice during cooking.
Stir in pineapple chunks and cashews.
Drain fish well.
Spoon sauce over. Microwave, uncovered, at High 1 to 2 minutes, or until thoroughly heated.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients until thick, then add the jello. Mix and cool.
Mix in fresh strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell; top with whipped topping.

title: cornbread
directions: Pour cooking oil in bottom of 8 or 9-inch round baking pan. Put oven on 350° and put baking pan in to preheat oil.
Mix cornmeal, egg, mayonnaise and enough milk to make mixture pour, but not too runny.
Once oil has been heated, pour in mixture and bake for about 40 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken and stuffing
directions: Make stuffing moist and put in a casserole dish.
Place chicken breasts on top; pour soup over chicken.
(Mix soup with a little water, 1/4 cup.)
Pour over chicken and stuffing and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a bowl, combine the sour cream, spinach, red pepper, onions, garlic, salt and hot pepper sauce. Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix wafers and margarine together.
Press into cake pan. Refrigerate.

title: antipasto bread
directions: Roll dough until flat.
Layer with ham, salami and cheese. Chop up artichoke hearts, mushrooms, eggplant and peppers.
Spread out over meats and cheese.
Sprinkle seasonings over everything. Roll up jelly roll style.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Peel zucchini; slice lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Slice as you would slice apples.
Add small amount of water; bring to a boil. Simmer until tender; drain well and cool.
Add remaining ingredients; place in an unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Cover with top crust; flute edges to seal.
Cut slits in top crust for steam to escape.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 40 to 50 minutes. (Tastes like apple pie.)

title: raisin nut pie
directions: Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Pour oil in electric deep fryer.
Preheat oven to 425° for 25 minutes.
Meanwhile, drain green chili peppers.
Discard seeds and cut into 12 strips.
Cut cheese into 2 cubes.
Wrap a chili strip around each cheese cube and dredge each in flour; set aside.

title: potato soup
directions: Prepare the potatoes, onions and carrots.
Place in saucepan. Add water, salt and pepper.
Cover and turn heat to high.
When boiling starts, switch to simmer and cook for 15 minutes.
Add milk; return heat to high and bring almost to a boil.
While this is heating, measure the flour into a bowl and break in the egg. Mix; stir the flour and egg mixture and the butter into the saucepan.
Return heat back to simmer and cook 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 5.

title: homos bi tahini(chickpea dip)
directions: Rinse and drain chickpeas; place in a blender with remaining ingredients.
Turn on blender, stopping to scrape sides of blender occasionally.
When well mixed, garnish with olive oil, parsley or ground red pepper.
Serve on pita bread.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jacob's "orange" pie
directions: Beat sweet potatoes real good.
Add milk and sugar.
Then add butter and eggs.
Put in oven for 5 minutes at 273°.
Take out and let cool.
Then eat.

title: split pea soup
directions: Put the end of a moderately lean smoked ham in a kettle with carrot and peeled onion, whole potatoes and boiling water.
Boil 1 hour and strain.
Now rinse the ham thoroughly in hot water and return to strained stock, together with split peas, which have been soaked overnight and boil for 1 hour.
Season with salt and white pepper and add catsup.
Serve at once.
Thin with boiling water if too thick.

title: stained glass salad
directions: Soak bananas 10 minutes in pineapple and orange juice.
Mix together remaining ingredients and refrigerate 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Brown sausage; drain and add cheese and other ingredients. Let cheese melt and mix well.
Let it cool a little and then spread on party rye.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in huge bowl and mash (squeeze), or, if mad, stomp on it.
Roll into small balls; put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of small glass; dip in granulated sugar and mash the balls flat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
This recipe can be cut in half.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Blend sugar and cake mix.
Add oil and sour cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour half the batter into greased and floured tube pan. Top with a mixture of the brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Add remainder of batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: granny's cornbread dressing
directions: Cook corn bread as directed.
Allow it to cool, then crumble. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican guadalupies
directions: Mix jumping beans and hot sauce together in old 50 gallon oil drum.
Let set for 24 hours.
Heat contents of oil drum to desired temperature and eat at will.
(Guaranteed to clear the gas out of your system!)

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar together until blended.
Next add flour, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Stir until well blended to wet ingredients.
Add vanilla and stir in.
Then add diced apples with peel and nuts.
Raisins can be added also, if you like. Blend well and pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream one cup sugar with a lump of butter the size of an egg. Have butter soft.
Beat 2 eggs in one cup of milk.
Mix baking powder and salt with flour.
Beat together smoothly.
Take a cup of blueberries, dust with flour and mix lightly with batter.
Put in muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: italian spinach
directions: Boil spinach and drain.
Saute garlic in butter and olive oil. Add spinach, Italian bread crumbs (to thicken), Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
You can top with boiled, sliced eggs.

title: vanilla wafer coconut balls
directions: Mix soft margarine and powdered sugar.
Add slightly soft orange juice.
Mix well.
Add pecans and crushed wafers.
Mix well and make into balls.
Roll into coconut.
Place on cookie sheet and chill.
Makes 72 balls.

title: camp stew
directions: Boil the potatoes and chopped onion.
When done, drain the liquid, reserving 1/4 cup for later use.
Combine all ingredients including liquid in a large pot.
Stir.
Let simmer for about 30 minutes.
(This can be done in an electric pot or crock-pot.)

title: spinach fandango
directions: Combine in large skillet beef, chopped onions, mushrooms, garlic, oregano and oil.
Brown and add salt and pepper. Place spinach on top and steam until mixable.
Mix the partially cooked ingredients in a medium casserole plus the soup and sour cream. Garnish with cheese. Bake uncovered 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: orange-basil linguine
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in small saucepan. Stir well. Bring to a boil and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add chopped basil and orange rind. Stir well.
Pour over linguine.
Toss gently to coat.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with orange slices and basil sprigs. Yields 6 servings.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in large bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, walnuts and bananas.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip pounded chicken into egg and then into bread crumbs, coating thoroughly.
In a medium skillet, heat olive oil.
Cook chicken in oil until done and well browned on both sides.
Pour spaghetti sauce into an 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Place chicken on sauce and top with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip to make a dressing.
Drain fruit cocktail, pineapple and oranges.
Mix. Add nuts and marshmallows.
Mix fruit with dressing and chill overnight.

title: impossible zucchini quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Mix the veggies, cheese and spices together and put in the plate.
In blender, mix the milk, Bisquick mix and eggs and blend until well mixed.
Pour over the veggies and stir gently.
Bake for 30 minutes or until a silver knife comes out pretty clean when inserted 1-inch from the edge.
Cool slightly and serve.
Good with a tossed salad and a crispy homemade bread.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add all other ingredients except macaroni and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Sprinkle each serving with Parmesan cheese.

title: quick taco salad
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain and remove from skillet.
In the same skillet, prepare Rice-A-Roni as package says.
Stir in meat mixture, salsa and chili powder.
Heat thoroughly.
Arrange lettuce on platter.
Top with rice mixture, tomato, cheese and tortilla chips.
Serves 5.

title: sweet-sour cabbage
directions: Heat pressure cooker.
Brown bacon.
Pour off excess drippings.
Add remaining ingredients.
Close cover securely. Place pressure regulator on vent pipe.
Cook 3 minutes.
Cool pressure cooker at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: helenann's bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove from skillet.
Add sliced onions and saute until translucent.
Add brown sugar, mustard and vinegar and simmer for 15 minutes.
Drain all the beans and add to mixture.
Mix.
Put in casserole; crumble bacon on top.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
You may adjust sweetness or tartness to taste by adding more sugar or vinegar.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
Mash bananas.
Beat in sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour.

title: orange chicken with toasted almonds
directions: Season chicken.
In two frying pans brown breasts in butter or margarine on both sides over medium heat.
Transfer all chicken to one pan.

title: corned beef treats(club member: nicholas thompson)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese. Spread on bread. Top with grated cheese. Place in oven under broil; let cook until cheese melts.

title: sticky chicken
directions: Combine soup mix, marmalade or preserves and Russian dressing. Dip chicken in mixture or let marinate for 1 to 4 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Extra marinade can be heated and poured over chicken at serving time.

title: loaf bread(makes 3 loaves)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and salt.
With a wire whisk, blend in Crisco until small flakes.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Grease sides of bowl, flip dough and cover. Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and knead five minutes.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Cut pork in 1/2-inch pieces; fry in skillet.
Season chicken and brown in oil.
Add onion and simmer until tender.
Cook rice, water and salt until dry and tender.
Add rice, parsley, green onions and sausage to chicken and simmer 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool macaroni.
Add chopped carrots, onion, chopped celery, pickles and chopped cheese.
Mix together mayonnaise, Eagle Brand milk and white vinegar.
Mix and pour over macaroni salad.

title: molasses brown bread(servings: 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Combine flour, wheat germ, brown sugar, salt and raisins in a mixing bowl. Mix well.

title: fruit bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter (oleo) and flour.
Spread chopped pecans on bottom of pan.
Melt 1 stick oleo in a double boiler; add light brown sugar.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add 1 cup flour, salt and vanilla.
Add beaten eggs; beat well.
Pour over pecans in pan.
Mix candied fruit; put evenly on top of other mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 325°; you might need 10 minutes more.
Let cool before cutting.

title: tuna muck
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Add cream of mushroom soup and drained tuna.
Cook until desired consistency.

title: exotic turkey salad
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the turkey, water chestnuts, grapes, celery and almonds.
Mix the curry powder, soy sauce and mayonnaise in a separate bowl.
Add to the other ingredients.

title: chicken corn chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Stir in soup mix. Simmer covered, stirring occasionally, 10 minutes.
Stir in corn and milk; heat.
Do not boil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chinese roast pork
directions: Mash garlic.
Mix with soy sauce, sugar and salt. Cut pork butt into 3 pieces, lengthwise.
Put meat in a shallow dish.
Pour garlic mixture over meat.
Let meat stand in the refrigerator for 1 hour.
Turn meat a few times. Remove meat from dish.
Lay pieces on a rack in an uncovered pan.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve hot or cold.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Make pudding according to directions on the box.
Cool.
When cool, beat pudding with mixer; add peanut butter and continue to beat until well blended.
Pour mixture into baked pie crust and let set in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.
Spread container of Cool Whip evenly over top of pie.
Garnish with peanuts, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend in food processor.
Baste chicken during last 5 minutes.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: *More or less flour, cheese and milk can be used, according to individual taste.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix
sugar,
flour,
evaporated
milk and milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook
over
medium heat until it begins to thicken, stirring
constantly.
Add eggs (slightly beaten) and continue cooking
until
thick.
Remove
from
heat and add vanilla and oleo.
Put a layer of vanilla wafers, then a layer of bananas, then a layer of pudding in a bowl.	Repeat until you have 3 or 4 layers;
end
with	pudding
on
the top.
Put some vanilla wafer crumbs on the top.	Refrigerate.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Combine berries and sugar in Dutch oven.
Mix well, let stand 3 to 4 hours.
Slowly bring to boil until sugar dissolves.
Stir in lemon juice.
Remove from heat and skim off foam with metal spoon.
Remove fruit from syrup with slotted spoon and place in shallow pan.
Bring syrup to boil, cook 10 minutes.
Pour syrup over berries.
Let stand 24 hours.
Shake pan occasionally so berries will absorb syrup and remain whole.
Place preserves into hot jars.
Makes 4 pints.

title: shrimp and cashew stir-fry
directions: Cook brown rice. Shell and devein the shrimp; set aside.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together and top with 4 ounces crushed potato chips. Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate chips together with a little salt.
Add Rice Krispies, as much as mixture will take.
Line 2 pie pans with the mixture and freeze.
When frozen, fill with ice cream.
Grate Baker's chocolate over top.
Serve soon after taking out of freezer.
Cut down with a fork.

title: 3 week sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Put into a covered bowl and refrigerate for up to 3 weeks.
When you want biscuits, just grease your hands.
Break off pieces of dough and form into biscuits.
Put on a greased pan or cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° or 425° for about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Whisk together the first 5 ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 275° for 15 minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Place chicken in a dish. Blend together soup and milk.
Place cheese on chicken; cover with soup mixture.
Top with croutons, bread crumbs or Ritz crackers. Bake, covered with foil, for 45 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: cheese tortellini with tomatoes and non-fat sour cream
directions: Heat oven to 500°.
Pound the chicken breasts to flatten slightly.
Combine mustard and wine in shallow dish.
Stir to blend.

title: peanut butter crunch icing
directions: Cook egg whites, brown sugar, cream of tartar and water over boiling water for 7 minutes or until icing holds peaks.
Beat constantly with beater.
Remove from heat; beat until cool. Sprinkle crushed peanut brittle over top of frosted cake.

title: pie dough for fried pies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 2 eggs and 1 large can Carnation milk.
Let stand overnight after mixing together.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
Mix with other ingredients and bake about 30 minutes.

title: fudge sauce that hardens
directions: Melt
chocolate
with
butter
in
a medium-sized heavy saucepan over
very low heat; stir in boiling water until well blended.
Add
sugar and corn syrup, mixing thoroughly.
Bring mixture
to
boiling, stirring constantly.
Lower heat; simmer until mixture thickens slightly, about 9 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool 15 minutes.
Stir in rum, blending well.

title: melon and cheese appetizer
directions: In small bowl, combine melon balls with wine.
Cover; chill about 1 hour.
Cut thinly sliced Prosciutto into strips, 3 inches long and 2 inches wide.
Wrap meat strips around each cheese wedge.
Drain melon balls.
On lettuce lined plate, arrange cheese wrapped Prosciutto and melon balls.
Garnish with alfalfa sprouts. Makes 8 servings.

title: cinnamon rolls in a jiffy
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, cake mix, yeast, salt and warm water in large bowl; mix well.
Add enough remaining flour to form soft dough.
Knead lightly on floured surface for 6 to 8 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Pat into 9 x 18-inch rectangle.
Spread with margarine; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up from long edge to enclose filling, sealing edge and ends.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Let rise, covered, in warm place for 15 minutes or until doubled in bulk. Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until brown.
May frost with confectioners sugar icing.
Yields 18.

title: apple streusel coffee bread
directions: Thaw
dough
according
to
package directions.
Divide dough in
half;
let rest 10 minutes.
On floured surface roll each dough
half
to
an
8-inch
square.
Spread
each with 1 tablespoon of
the
softened
butter.
Arrange half the apples down the center of each dough square.
Combine brown sugar and cinnamon;
sprinkle over apples.
Cutting toward filling, make 2-inch long cuts in dough at 1-inch intervals on both sides of apples.
Fold
strips alternately over apples; fold under ends of loaf.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased 9 x 13 in. casserole dish.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour or until pudding is set and top is browned very lightly.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: turkey macaroni salad
directions: Mix together and place one cup of mixture on a lettuce leaf. This makes a salad for 8 servings.

title: pie crust(makes two pie crusts)
directions: Sour milk and set aside.
Using a pastry blender, mix flour, Crisco and salt.
Add sour milk and blend to proper consistency.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl, except nuts.
Beat on medium speed until smooth.
Fold in nuts.
Pour in greased pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook the
lasagna noodles in boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain
and
rinse under cold water.
Brown the meat. Grate the
cheeses.
Prepare the sauce by combining the tomato sauce, parsley, basil and garlic to taste.

title: first lady's crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together, except Cheddar cheese. Place evenly in a casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Add milk until thick but not stiff.
Dip with tablespoon; drop into hot and boiling chicken broth.
Stir each time you drop.
If dumplings are too large, chip them with side of spoon.
Boil until dumplings are done.
Add chicken.

title: snow balls
directions: Cook together in heavy saucepan for 5 minutes the first 4 ingredients.
Remove from fire and add the next 2 ingredients.

title: juicy meat balls
directions: Mix well.
Form into 2 inch meat balls.
Brown	on
all sides in hot shortening.	Place in casserole.
Bake
in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.	Makes 12 meat balls.

title: vanilla cream pudding with fruit
directions: In blender, mix milk, pudding, yogurt and vanilla and blend until smooth.
Mix all fruits.
Layer 4 dessert dishes, alternating with pudding and fruit, ending with pudding.
Top with 1 raspberry, 1 strawberry and kiwi.
Garnish with orange peel and mint.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate.
Serves 4. Contains 110 calories, 1 gm fat and 384 mg sodium.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pastry pie shell.
Cool and top with whipped cream or ice cream or serve plain.

title: mrs. edwards' fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add spices, milk and egg whites; mix well.
Sift flour and baking powder; add fruit and nuts to flour mixture.
Stir into creamed mixture; blend well.
Pour into 5 greased and floured 8-inch round pans.
Bake in slow oven, 325° for 40 minutes or until cakes spring back when lightly touched with finger.

title: reuben dip
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat through.
Serve warm on small party rye bread.

title: no crust fruit pie
directions: Slice any firm, ripe, raw fruit into 9-inch pan to fill.
Mix cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar together and sprinkle over fruit.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except egg whites, in one bowl.
Beat for 5 minutes on low speed.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in cake mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Turn out on rack.
Have glaze ready and apply while cake is hot.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine meats, crumbs, pepper, eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Form a loaf in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: buttermilk refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in melted shortening.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients and buttermilk to yeast mixture; mix well.
Turn dough out on a well-floured surface.
Knead gently until dough can be handled.
Shape into a ball.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and refrigerate until needed.
(Dough will keep 1 week.)
Shape dough into rolls as desired.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: quick manicotti
directions: Cook and rinse shells. Cook hamburger, oregano and garlic together. Add Mozzarella cheese and mayonnaise and stuff shells. Arrange in greased 13 x 9 pan. Pour spaghetti sauce over the shells and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake for 15 minutes at 350°. Cook an additional 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: rainbow frappe
directions: Let 1 container of sherbet soften at room temperature for 10 minutes.
In large punch bowl pour half of juices and ginger ale. Add scoops of softened sherbet, using all of 1/2 gallon.
Do not stir.
Repeat same process in another punch bowl.
Makes 2 bowls frappe.

title: spinach cheese casserole
directions: Cook spinach just until barely tender.
Rinse and drain to as dry as possible, lightly pressing between paper towels if necessary.
Set aside in large bowl.
Melt 4 ounces cream cheese in the mushroom soup, stirring carefully so it doesn't scorch. Stir in the onion and add whole mixture to spinach.
Stir well and set aside. Use rolling pin to crush crackers between 2 pieces of waxed paper. Melt margarine and stir in cracker crumbs.
Pour spinach mixture into casserole dish and top with cracker mixture, spreading evenly.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes.

title: breakfast brunch casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain and crumble. Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam and spread bread. Sprinkle sausage over bread cubes. Beat eggs, milk, salt, mustard and cheese together. Pour over bread/sausage mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, oil, squash and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add nuts. Divide into 2 greased bread pans or muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: granny's tomato relish
directions: Be careful in your selection; do not choose too young; and take only such as have been reared in a good moral atmosphere. Some insist on keeping them in a pickle, while others keep them in hot water. This only makes them sour, hard and sometimes bitter. Even poor varieties may be made tender, sweet and good by garnishing them with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste. Then wrap them in a mantle of charity, keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
When thus prepared, they should keep for years.

title: cake with variations
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar and water until very light and foamy. Whip egg whites to which you have added 1 pinch of salt and 1 teaspoon of water until stiff.
Beat 3 teaspoons of confectioners sugar, one at a time, into egg whites.

title: creamy cheesy potatoes
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with Pam. Mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into pan. Sprinkle with mashed potato chips. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: french cheese braid
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs, margarine and 2 cups of the flour.
Beat until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to make the dough easy to handle. Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl; turn greased side up.
Cover. Let rise until double, 1 to 2 hours.
Punch down dough, knead in cheese and divide into 3 equal parts.
Roll each part into a rope, 15 inches long.
Place ropes together on a greased cookie sheet. Braid ropes gently and loosely.
Do not stretch.
Pinch ends to fasten; tuck under.
Brush with oil.
Let rise 40 to 50 minutes. Heat oven to 375°.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes and stand up in deep dish.
Pour soup mixture over potatoes and cover.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, then remove cover and bake 10 more minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos in food processor.
Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese; set aside.
Mix pudding and milk until smooth.
Combine mixtures.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer in an 8-inch flowerpot. Start with Oreos and end with Oreos.
Garnish with gummy worms and silk flowers.
Add garden spade to serve.

title: homemade egg substitute
directions: Beat egg whites lightly.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well together.
Makes 4 quarter cup servings.
Can be stored in refrigerator for one week if eggs are fresh.
After this it can be frozen.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil first four ingredients 1 1/2 minutes, then add the other three ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Place cracker crumbs over margarine.
Cover crumbs with coconut.
Add chocolate pieces next.
Cover with pecans. Pour milk over top.
Do not stir.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool in pan. Cut into squares.

title: six layer casserole
directions: Put in greased casserole in layers as given.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Bake, covered, 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inch.
Combine baking mix, sugar, flour, egg, milk and orange peel.
Beat vigorously 1/2 minute.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly before slicing. Wrap any leftover bread tightly in aluminum foil.

title: frozen cheese tort(gone with the wind)
directions: Mix graham crackers, cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and butter or oleo and press into pan to form crust.
Reserve some for topping.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Reserve 1/2 cup shredded Mozzarella and 1/2 cup pizza sauce for topping later.
In large bowl, mix remaining cheese and pizza sauce with ground beef, bread crumbs and eggs.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, shape meat mixture into 9 x 5-inch loaf, pressing firmly.
Bake meat loaf 30 minutes.
Pour reserved pizza sauce over top of loaf.
Bake 30 minutes longer, sprinkling with shredded cheese during last 10 minutes of baking time.
To serve, lift out of pan and garnish with parsley.
Serves 8.
Each serving - 420 calories, 26 g. fat.

title: freezer corn
directions: Combine all ingredients and put into freezer bags.
When you thaw for dinner, you only need add your shortening and seasonings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan (or 1-quart casserole).
Put rest of ingredients in double boiler and melt slowly.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle dressing on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add oil, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Slice cake in pan.
Pour icing over it while it is still hot.

title: spiced tea
directions: Steep for 5 minutes the tea bags.
Add 2 cups water, sugar and cinnamon stick.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Boil five minutes.
Serve.

title: stuffed italian chicken rolls
directions: Pound chicken breasts to 1/2-inch thickness.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Dip each chicken breast into egg mixture and then roll in bread crumbs.
Spray olive oil on both sides of chicken breast.
Sprinkle garlic powder and Italian seasoning on one side, then add a layer of shredded cheese.
Tightly roll up and place into a casserole dish with seam down.
When finished placing all the chicken breasts in the dish, spray olive oil on all of the chicken rolls very well.
Bake in oven at 400° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: devil's food cake
directions: *Whole milk and 1 tablespoon vinegar.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Top with crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° until browned and set.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cut slice from top of bread.
Remove center, leaving 1-inch shell.
Cut removed bread into bite size pieces.

title: chicken rice
directions: Place rice in greased 10 x 8-inch baking dish, cover with vegies and seasonings.
Combine soup and mayonnaise gradually. Add water until well blended.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture on.
Top with chicken and remaining soup mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: roast beef
directions: Place meat in a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour the tomato juice over top and add water to barely cover beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 3 hours. Use the juice of baked beef and thicken for a gravy.

title: pride of iowa sausage bake
directions: Beat eggs; add milk and crumbled sausage.
Add corn, bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix and bake in covered dish at 375° about 1 hour until done.

title: cheesy chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a buttered 2 quart casserole, mix all
ingredients,
except
shrimp.
Cover and bake 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Add shrimp, pushing well down into the mixture.
Re-cover and bake 1/2
hour
longer or until rice is done. Serves 4.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom.
Mix cake mix according to directions on the box.
Pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix together oleo, cream cheese and sugar. Spoon in globs on top of cake by teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: michigan rocks(cookies)
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and cinnamon together.
Add eggs, flour, vanilla and baking soda.
Mix well and add dates, walnuts and grapes.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: yule logs
directions: Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla. Form into "logs" about 2 inches long and 1/2 inch in diameter. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: green tomato soy
directions: Slice but do not peel tomatoes.
Mix all the ingredients together and cook slowly until vegetables are tender, stirring often to prevent scorching.
It will take about 1 1/2 hours.
Pour into clean hot jars and seal at once.

title: raymond stoiber's ramen noodle salad
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, noodles, almonds and sesame seed together in a skillet on low heat until all the noodles are thoroughly covered.
Cool.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except sauce mix.
Press meat in tube pan and spread sauce over top.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 to 11 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar and salad oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add carrots and beat one minute.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red devil franks
directions: Cook onion and garlic in fat over low heat until onion is tender, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add all other ingredients.
Continue heating until flavors are well blended. Split franks halfway through lengths.
Lay split side up in pan or baking dish.
Spoon sauce over franks and heat until broiler until tender.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and blend.
Add food coloring, water and cocoa.
Blend in buttermilk; add flour gradually.
Add vanilla and heat until mixed.
Mix vinegar and soda and stir in last; do not beat.
Pour into three 9-inch pans. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Frost with Fluff Frosting.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix together well.
Place in glass pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with cocktail rye bread.

title: shrimp wiggle
directions: In large nonstick skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter over moderate high heat.
Add red pepper and mushrooms; saute for 5 minutes.
Using slotted spoon, transfer to plate.
Add shrimp to skillet and cook for 3 minutes, until shrimp are opaque.
Transfer to plate with vegetables.
Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter, stir in flour and paprika.
Cook until bubbly.
Whisk in milk and cook, stirring constantly, 3 minutes longer, until sauce thickens. Stir in peas, salt, pepper, vegetables and shrimp and heat through.
At last minute, stir in hard-cooked egg gently.
Ladle over toast points.

title: homemade cocoa mix
directions: Stir all ingredients together and store in a tightly closed jar or container for up to two months.

title: chocolate dip
directions: Combine cocoa and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Add water, stirring until smooth.
Stir in corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat until boiling, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and stir until melted.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool mixture to room temperature.
Serve with whole strawberries.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: micro spaghetti sauce
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, cook beef, mushrooms, onions and garlic on High for 5 minutes, stirring to break up meat.
Drain off fat. Stir in tomatoes, paste, water, sugar, salt, basil, thyme, oregano and pepper.
Cook, covered, on High 8 minutes.
Stir well, then cook on Medium for 10 minutes.
Stir, then serve.

title: jook
directions: Pick and remove meat from turkey; reserve.
Break up carcass and put in large pot.
Cover with water; add next 4 ingredients and simmer at least 2 hours.
Longer is better even overnight. Strain stock; discard all solids.
Add reserved turkey meat, green onions and rice.
Cook 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Add shoyu.
Put chopped lettuce in bowls and fill with hot soup and serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Brown butter over medium heat.
Beat eggs well and add other ingredients.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of unbaked pie shell. Cook for 50 minutes at 325°.
Double for 2 pies.

title: peach praline pie
directions: Mix the peaches, sugar and tapioca in a large bowl and let stand for several minutes. Combine the flour and brown sugar in a small bowl. Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly. Stir in pecans. Sprinkle 1/3 of the mixture over pastry shell and top with peaches. Sprinkle with remaining peach mixture. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce to 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix and add ice cubes as desired and 1 pint lime or lemon sherbet in each punch bowl.

title: ghostly brew
directions: Combine candies and water.
Bring to a boil; boil until candies are melted.
Cool.
Just before serving, combine liquid, Punch and club soda in punch bowl.
Add ice cubes; float apples in punch.
Makes 10 cups.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Then add pineapple.
(Do not drain pineapple.)
Bake at 350°.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Mix all in crock-pot and cook slowly all day.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, water, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes. Cool.
Meanwhile, mix other ingredients in a bowl. Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables. This will keep for 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt 2 sticks margarine in a saucepan.
Add peanut butter. When melted, add confectioners sugar.
Spread in greased pan. Melt 1 stick margarine with chocolate chips.
Pour on top of peanut butter mixture.
Let set.

title: ice cream in a coffee can
directions: Little did I know when I married into the Kimbrel family what I was getting into.
Having married in Wichita, many of the Klan could not attend so Pat and I graciously took our wedding cake to share with them in Coffeyville.
Dorothy, Mel and Darrel sent Pat and I on a phony trip to town.
When we returned, we discovered, upon beginning to cut the symbolic cake, that those onery people had already eaten out the middle of the cake.
It was then that I learned what to expect from my new family.
Some day I'm going to get back at them!!!!!
So watch out....

title: beef louise
directions: Cut meat into bite-size pieces, cutting away all fat.
Combine with other ingredients and bake in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, covered.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding mix with corn syrup. Add milk and egg, stirring to blend. Add nuts. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 375° until top is firm, about 40 minutes.

title: special k candy
directions: Combine Karo and sugar in saucepan and bring to rolling boil, then
add
peanut
butter
and
cereal.
Mix and drop by teaspoons on wax paper to cool.

title: almond butter
directions: Blend
smooth and creamy.
May have to stop blender and stir. If not blending, add water.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain juice from pears, saving juice.
Heat one cup of juice and add jello; stir until dissolved.
While still hot, stir in cream cheese which has been brought to room temperature and softened with cream or milk until smooth.
Chill until partially set.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Prepare crust of cheese cake according to directions on package; add cinnamon.
Prepare filling according to directions on box and then add (using mixer) the sour cream, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate before serving.
Top with a can of prepared cherry pie filling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: basic muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Grease 12 muffin cups. Set aside.
Break egg into bowl.
Beat lightly with fork.
Stir in milk and shortening. Add flour and sugar.
Stir just until blended. Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan or skillet, saute bacon until brown and crisp.
Remove.
Drain on paper towels.
Dice or crumble.
In same skillet saute chopped onion and potatoes for a couple of minutes.
Sprinkle with flour.
Add clam juice from cans and from bottle.
Stir to combine.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, stirring from time to time, until potatoes are soft, about 15 minutes.
Add half and half and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add minced clams.
Heat until simmering.
Do not boil.
Add whipping cream, if used.
Sprinkle with parsley or diced bacon.
Serve immediately. Good with croutons or small crackers.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken, broccoli and rice
directions: Mix all together.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Cook in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes, covered.
Last 15 minutes, cook uncovered.

title: sesame cheese muffins
directions: Mix biscuit mix and half the cheese.
Cook onion in 1 tablespoon of fat until just tender.
Combine egg, milk and onion; add all at once to biscuit mixture.
Stir until moistened.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Thaw one 12 to 25 pound turkey in refrigerator 3 days before. The day before, start turkey before supper.
Place 40 pounds of charcoal in lowest pan of smoker; put water in middle pan and always keep both charcoal and water full.
Put turkey on top rack. Add hickory chips to charcoal all during cooking time.
Should be done next day between noon and dinner.

title: apple brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large bowl.
Whisk oil and eggs in another bowl until blended and smooth.
Stir in sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until blended.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until top is golden and a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool completely. Cut in 40 squares.
Serves 40.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Mix the 1/4 cup sugar and the 1 tablespoon flour together and add this to the sliced peaches, stirring it through.
Stir the remaining ingredients together; mix well and sprinkle on the peaches.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Delicious with whipped cream or served warm on ice cream.

title: carrot salad
directions: In large bowl combine tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar, oil, salt, mustard and pepper; stir until blended.
Add carrots, onion and green pepper; stir to mix well.
Cover and chill, preferably overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Cook and brown meat and half of the onions until tender. Drain excess grease.
Stir in chili powder, salt, remaining onions, kidney beans, tomatoes and tomato sauce. Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes.
Top with shredded cheese, if desired. Excellent chili, not too spicy!

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, then add cold water.
Mix softened cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise.
When gelatin is cool (not set), add cream cheese mixture to it and blend well. Add cucumbers, onion and pineapple.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat until smooth.
Add shrimp and mix well.
Serve with chips, crackers or fresh vegetables.

title: deep fry batter for veggies
directions: Mix well together.
Deep fry in hot oil or crisco in your fry daddy.

title: sparkling punch
directions: You will also need an ice ring with pineapple chunks or citrus slices and fresh mint leaves embedded in it.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Cube 3 slices of bread and place in bottom of casserole.
Cover with mixture of chicken, onion, celery, salad dressing, salt and pepper.
Place 6 slices of bread over the mixture.

title: nut muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin cups.
Sift together flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
In mixing bowl, beat egg until foamy.
Add milk and melted fat.
Add milk mixture to dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts. Stir until mixture is moist, but slightly lumpy.
Fill muffin cups, 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: microwave brownies
directions: Grease 8-inch square heat resistant, non-metallic baking dish. Sift together flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat until smooth. Pour batter into dish.
Heat uncovered on roast for 8 to 9 minutes in microwave.
Test for doneness with toothpick; cook longer if needed.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Cook on High 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and stir in 1/2 teaspoon soda.

title: banana whoopie pies
directions: Stir dry ingredients together.
Cream shortening and sugar. Add eggs.
Add bananas and dry ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet (makes 20 Whoopie Pies).
Bake in oven at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: Mix avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Layer all these ingredients in order given in a casserole dish and chill a couple of hours before serving so it will be fresh.
Serve with tortilla chips or Fritos.
Great for parties or anytime.

title: lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions.
Drain. Combine sausage, onion and garlic.
Cook until sausage is no longer pink, stirring often to break sausage apart; drain. Reserve 2/3 cup of tomato sauce.
Stir remaining tomato sauce, the tomato paste, water, basil, oregano and marjoram into meat mixture.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 5 minutes.
Combine Ricotta, spinach, Parmesan, eggs and salt.
Mix well.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Spray a baking dish with cooking spray and cover the bottom with a layer of dried beef. Top with chicken pieces.
Mix mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes a wonderful gravy!

title: mock steak
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, milk, hamburger and seasonings and let stand overnight.
Fry and put in roaster and put mushroom soup with a little milk over it.
Bake 2 hours.
Put cheese over it before serving.

title: baked ham, grits and eggs
directions: Prepare ham flavored grits according to package directions, using the 2 cups of water.
Stir in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Pour grits mixture into ungreased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish. Crack each egg and place on top of grits, spacing about 2 inches apart.
Melt the remaining 2 tablespoons of butter.
Pour melted butter over eggs and sprinkle with pepper.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 20 minutes or until done. Serve immediately.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Dip bread in small amount of water and mix well with other ingredients.
Put in greased pan and place bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: i can't believe it's a cookie
directions: Mix ingredients; roll into a small ball.
Use a fork to press the ball into flat cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over boiling water. Remove from heat.
Add condensed milk and peanuts or raisins and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered baking sheet or plate.
Chill for several hours.
Serve.

title: mango bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add nuts and mix well.
Make a well in the dry ingredients. Beat eggs.
Add vanilla and oil.
Mix well.
Add egg mixture into the well.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Add mango; mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan and let ingredients stand for 20 minutes before baking. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: slime
directions: Dissolve food coloring in water; add baking soda and cornstarch.
It's just like the real thing!
Great fun for little ones!

title: gramma's sour cream cookies
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Mix all others together.
Blend the dry ingredients with the moist.
Roll out on a floured surface with a rolling pin.
Dough should be about 1/2-inch thick.
Use a cookie cutter or small glass to cut out cookies.
Bake at 350°. The bottom of the cookies should be a light brown when done.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place chicken in baking dish. Cover with sauce and bake on low heat until done.
You can double ingredients for 2 chickens.

title: pecan pie
directions: Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pot roast
directions: Melt butter in pressure cooker.
Brown roast on both sides. Salt to taste.
Pour the onion soup over the meat.
Slice the onion on top of the meat.
Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Cook for about 1 hour at 10 pounds pressure.
Thicken the gravy with cornstarch.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, mixing well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Cover with cherry pie filling or other favorite fruit topping.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed using lettuce on bottom and dressing on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Chill and toss before serving.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix dry milk, cocoa, sugar and salt.
Label and store in tightly covered container at room temperature, no longer than 6 months.

title: mini b.l.t.'s(appetizers)
directions: Put
layer of Miracle Whip on crackers.
Sprinkle bacon bits on	top.
Put 1/2 small cherry tomato on top.
(Watch so when you take a bite, the tomatoes don't "squirt" on you.)

title: apple-acorn squash(5 grams sodium per serving)
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly oil large baking dish.
Place squash, cut side down, in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes; turn right side up.

title: lasagna
directions: Combine hamburger, onion and garlic cloves.
Brown in skillet and add chili powder, tomato sauce, tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Cook lasagna noodles until done. Layer meat and noodles in a medium sized square cake pan, adding cheese to the top layer.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake until cheese melts.
Serves 4.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon cheesecake with raspberry topping
directions: Combine crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup sugar, mixing well; press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 7 minutes. Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup boiling water; add lemon juice.
Chill until partially set; whip until light.
