Combine cream cheese, remaining sugar and vanilla, beating well; combine with lemon mixture.
Whip evaporated milk; fold into cream cheese mixture. Pour into crumb-lined pan.
Cook dessert mix with 1 cup water until thickened; add frozen raspberries.
Stir until thawed; spread on cheesecake.
Chill in refrigerator; cut in squares. Yields 12 servings.

title: perfect peppermint patties
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls and place on a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Flatten with a glass to 1/4-inch; chill for 30 minutes.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Stir together sugar and Miracle Whip.
Add flour, soda and cocoa.
Add water and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: delight-full peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients except red peppers.
Cut peppers lengthwise and hollow out.
Fill with stuffing mixture.
Place in baking pan.
Cover and bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
Remove cover; bake for 10 more minutes.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown ground beef, bacon and onion; drain.
Mix brown sugar, liquid smoke, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add meat and onion.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook 4 to 6 hours.

title: shrimp or crawfish pasta salad
directions: Boil seafood just to color red (do not overcook).
Remove from water, drain and set aside to cool.
Boil noodles, onion, celery and bell pepper in same water until noodles are done.
Drain.
Put in large bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Add mayonnaise enough to mix well.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Put soda in hot water.
Mix with buttermilk.
Set aside. Cream oleo, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Add lemon juice.
Add buttermilk mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crabmeat cheese muffin appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on slightly pretoasted muffin halves.
Chill overnight.
Cut into appetizer-sized pieces when chilled.
Then broil to melt everything.
Serve warm.

title: cauliflower-olive salad
directions: Chop flowerets of cauliflower.
Add olives and green olives. Add mayonnaise to taste.

title: ma's brown sugar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked crust. Bake in slow oven until set.
NO HOT OVEN.

title: orange sunshine salad
directions: Combine first four ingredients in large Pyrex bowl.
(Be sure water is hot enough to dissolve jello.)
Place in microwave; heat to boiling, stirring occasionally, and boil for 3 minutes. Mixture should be thickened.
Let cool to room temperature and add oranges and fold in Cool Whip until smooth.
Can also be frozen and cut into squares and served as a dessert.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Drain. Add tomato sauce, ketchup, salt and pepper.
Get hot and then pour into casserole dish. Add cheese and put biscuits on top.
Put in a 425° oven. Cook 20 minutes or until biscuits are done and brown.

title: spaghetti squash primavera(makes 4 servings: carb count: 13 grams)
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Add garlic. Cook and stir 3 minutes. Add onion, carrot and peppers. Cook and stir 3 minutes. Add tomatoes, yellow squash, zucchini, corn, oregano and thyme. Cook 5 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally. Cut spaghetti squash lengthwise in half. Remove seeds.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 9 minutes or until squash separates easily into strands when tested with fork.

title: rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly in large bowl. Let set to rise. When dough has risen to top of bowl, punch down with spoon. Add lid to bowl and refrigerate over night. Next morning take out dough and roll in flour. Cut out rolls and let set 1 hour and cook. Cook on 400°about 15 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add oats and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no water salad mold
directions: Heat pineapple juice to boiling.
Dissolve jellos in juice and cool.
After jello mixture is cooled, add other ingredients and jell.

title: brownie ice cream cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add eggs and chocolate topping and mix well.
Stir in flour, vanilla and salt.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Spread with softened ice cream.
Freeze for 2 hours. Before serving, swirl with more chocolate topping and whipped cream.
If allowed to freeze longer than 2 hours, let sit at room temperature for 15 minutes before serving.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Coat tops of pork
chops with Italian bread crumbs.
Place in covered dish in oven.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.
Very easy, very moist!

title: pink cherry salad
directions: Mix pie filling, pineapple, pecans and milk together.
Add Cool Whip.
Freeze and serve.

title: drunken dogs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in crock-pot.
Add wieners and onion.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on low heat for 1 hour.

title: kimberly's venison casserole
directions: Brown venison and onion.
Boil potatoes (sliced very thin) until tender.
Layer the ingredients in a deep dish, meat, potatoes, soup until all used.
Cook at 300°.
After it has cooked, pour cheese on top. This can be changed by adding chopped green pepper and using cream of chicken soup.

title: "big boy" strawberry pie
directions: Boil until thick the water, sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Then add strawberry jello.
If not red enough, use red food coloring. Cool.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into baked shell.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: italian love cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions; put into a 9 x 13 inch pan.
In a bowl, beat together until well mixed, the eggs, sugar, vanilla and Ricotta cheese.
Spoon mixture onto the batter and spread with a knife.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and let sit at least 2 hours.

title: do-not-salt chop suey
directions: Brown hamburg; add next 9 ingredients.
Rinse each can from soup with 1/4 can of water.
Mix all and put into casserole.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine carrots, pineapple, sweet potatoes, egg whites and sugars.
Mix well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Coat dates and walnuts with a small amount of flour mixture.
Combine flour mixture with carrot mixture.
Mix well.
Add dates and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Store in refrigerator.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
In a small saucepan, boil sugar and water until syrup spins a thread when spoon is lifted from mixture.
Quickly pour hot syrup into egg white, beating with electric mixer.
Add raspberries and continue beating.
Spoon this over squares of yellow cake.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring butter, water and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from heat. Mix chocolate mixture with flour and salt.
Add beaten eggs and remaining ingredients.
Pour into large, greased 17 x 11-inch cookie sheet with sides.
Bake
20 to 22 minutes at 375°.

title: brazil nut dressing
directions: May add one or more cups of water.
Mix together and stuff in every cranny of large turkey (20 to 25 pound bird).

title: pink jello salad(sugar-free)
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberry jello.
Cool slightly.
Add buttermilk.
Refrigerate until jello begins to gel.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until sets.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Lightly grease an 8-inch square dish with butter wrapper; set aside.
Sift sugar and cocoa together into microwave-safe bowl. Place butter on top of dry mixture.
Do not stir at this time. Add milk and cook 2 minutes on Full power.
Stir.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour immediately in an 8-inch square dish and refrigerate until set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, beat together sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix in orange rind and vanilla.
Stir together in another bowl flour(s), cinnamon, salt, baking powder, baking soda and nutmeg.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Stir into batter alternately zucchini, making 3 additions of dry ingredients and 2 of zucchini.
Transfer to greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes in pan.
Turn out to cool on wire rack.
Wrap in foil or Saran.
Better the next day.

title: krazy krunch
directions: Set popcorn aside.
Mix together and boil other ingredients 10 minutes on low heat.
Drizzle over popcorn.
Mix thoroughly.

title: layered hamburger pie(for one 9-inch pie; 4 servings)
directions: Mix beef with egg, crumbs, salt, herbs, mustard, cumin and garlic powder.
Put into pie pan to make crust.
Fill crust with a layer of potatoes, onion and mushrooms.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and remove foil.
Top with cheese and sprinkle with parsley.
Return to oven just long enough to melt cheese.

title: summore cookies(christmas)
directions: Mix together
Rice
Krispies and sugar, then add melted oleo and peanut	butter.
Mix
thoroughly and form into balls; size of walnuts.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Cook rhubarb and cherries with 2 cups of sugar until rhubarb is falling apart.
Add the dry jello and chill.
Add nuts after mixture is chilled.
This salad is very tart and nippy and will not completely set.
Excellent for ice cream topping or cake.

title: quick biscuits
directions: *Use any combination of whole wheat, unbleached, oat flour or corn meal, mixed bran, wheat germ or rolled oats.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Combine, chill and serve.

title: pasta sauce
directions: Skin and chop tomatoes.
Wash and chop basil.
Halve garlic. Mix ingredients and let sit at room temperature at least 1 hour.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and put in pie shell.
Sprinkle on topping made of remaining ingredients.
Mix with pastry blender until fine.
Put on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in regular oven or microwave 10 minutes and finish in convection oven at 325° for 20 minutes or regular oven at 350° until done and crust has browned.

title: mrs. upton's ham pie
directions: Saute minced onion and bell pepper.
Make cream sauce with 2 tablespoons flour, butter, 2 cups milk and soup.
Add ham, onion and bell pepper to cream sauce.
Make biscuit dough with remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with cheese biscuits. Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: easy fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk, butter and salt to
boil. Stir continuously for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until chips are melted.
Pour into buttered pan. Chill until firm; cut in squares.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream very fresh butter and sugar together.
(If butter is not fresh, your shortbread will have a very unpleasant taste).
Batter is very dry and crumbly.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased pan. Press dough with the back of a spoon until smooth.
Prick with a fork.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cut while still warm.
Can be frozen.
Dough can be sprinkled with granulated sugar or sesame seeds before baking for variety.

title: everything sauce
directions: In a large frying pan, lightly saute all ingredients over medium heat. When mixture begins to brown, remove from heat and drain off fat.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Clean and slice mushrooms.
Combine ingredients and pour over mushrooms.
Marinate at least overnight, mixing occasionally.

title: creamed peas
directions: Heat peas, flour and butter until hot.
Pour in milk; stir often.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: diet butterfinger
directions: Mix together. Form into small balls.

title: light doughnuts
directions: Prewarm oven at 250° for 5 minutes and then turn off.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and drain broccoli; break into small flowerets. Add next 3 ingredients and toss. Add water chestnuts, if desired. Mix last 3 ingredients until sugar is dissolved. Add dressing over broccoli 30 minutes before serving.

title: russian spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and enjoy.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Mix 2 cups of flour, baking powder, salt, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, vanilla, egg, milk and butter.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch or 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Stir in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in orange peel, lemon peel, orange juice and egg just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Spread in pan.
Bake 8-inch loaf 1 hour 15 minutes; 9-inch loaf 55 to 65 minutes or 2 loaves in 7 1/2 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/4-inch for 40 minutes or cook until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen sides of loaf pan.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: nun's cake
directions: Grease 1 large tube pan very well with only butter and coat with cinnamon; set aside.
Cream well butter and granulated sugar. Add well beaten eggs.
Add in threes cake flour, salt, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add grated chocolate.
If desired, add black walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes, then invert pan.
Icing is not needed.
A little 10x sugar can be sifted over top of cake.

title: coca-cola pork
directions: Mix Coke, garlic and soy sauce in Pyrex dish.
Marinate meat in mixture several hours or overnight.
Turn meat several times.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and chill.
Chill ginger ale and mix before serving.
May substitute raspberry or orange Kool-Aid.
May substitute 3 bottles Fresca, Seven-Up or Sprite for ginger ale.

title: walnut pie
directions: Beat eggs until blended but not frothy.
Beat in corn syrup, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt.
Stir in nuts and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes before checking.
It may be necessary to bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chow mein(chicken or turkey)
directions: Mix onion soup by directions on box.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Add other ingredients and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over rice with chow mein noodles.

title: medium white sauce
directions: In saucepan, stir milk into cornstarch. Add margarine, salt and pepper, stirring constantly. Bring to boil over medium heat. Boil 1 minute. Makes 1 cup.

title: scottish trifle
directions: Slice jelly roll and line the bottom of a large decorative bowl or dish (slices should be approximately 1-inch thick). Drain oranges; save the juice.
Spread oranges on top of jelly roll in even layers.

title: crispy chicken livers
directions: In skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from skillet and crumble; set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together by hand until well mixed.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Tear angel food cake into small pieces.
Layer in punch bowl, beginning with cake, pudding, strawberry jello, strawberries and Cool Whip until all ingredients are layered.

title: seafoam punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid, sugar and milk in large punch bowl.
Spoon ice cream by small spoonfuls.
Carefully pour in lemon-lime drink. Serve immediately.
Makes 15 servings.

title: cocoa-oatmeal cookies(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, margarine, yogurt, water, vanilla, chocolate extract and egg whites in large bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes. Makes about 5 1/2 dozen.

title: picadillo(boiled ground beef)
directions: Brown garlic in hot oil and stir in onion and tomatoes for 3 minutes.
Add ground beef and cook until brown. Season with salt and pepper.
Add water.
Come and let boil for 10 minutes.
Taste and season if needed.
Add in potato and cook until done.
Serves 5.

title: shrimp and crab meat pasta
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Saute onions and bell peppers. Add shrimp.
Saute until pink and reduce fire.
Add heavy cream, milk, and cheese.
Add crab meat.
Add seasonings.
Cook until crab meat flakes apart.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: mound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco; add cocoa mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla; pour into 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: four layer pie
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 1/2 cup pecans.
Press into oblong cooking dish.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: philly free 3-step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix just until blended.
Do not overbeat after adding eggs.
Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray; sprinkle bottom with crumbs. Pour cream cheese mixture into prepared pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain salmon.
Combine salmon with eggs, oats, onion, parsley, lemon juice, mustard and pepper.
Add liquid drained from salmon or a small amount of skim milk, if needed, to form patties.
Cook in nonstick skillet until golden brown on both sides.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: tea dainties
directions: Trim crust
off
bread;
cut
bread
in strips, about 5 strips per slice.	Put
strips of bread and crust in 200° oven and dry out until crisp (1 to 2 hours).
Mix peanut butter and Wesson oil together
until it makes thin paste-thin enough to dip the crisp bread strips in.
Put bread crust in blender to make crumbs
or crush with rolling pin.
Mix bread crumbs with sugar, about
half and
half.	Roll
dipped
peanut strips in bread crust
crumbs and
sugar	(or graham cracker crumbs and sugar).
Store in tight container.	Keeps well.

title: four grain salad
directions: Cook each of the grains according to package directions. Drain and cool slightly; mix together.
Mix in celery, onions, garlic, green pepper and olives.
Pour olive oil over (just enough to coat the mixture).
Sprinkle on some, a tablespoon or so. Season and taste to adjust seasonings and dressing to your liking. (Vinegar could be red wine vinegar or could use part wine vinegar and balsamic.)

title: pumpkin roll(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Blend together.
Line jellyroll pan with waxed paper.
Pour mixture on.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on clean tea towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Roll up while warm.
Let cool, then open and fill with Filling.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and cut up broccoli, discarding tough stems.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Mix broccoli, onion, bacon, water chestnuts and raisins in bowl.
In a separate bowl make dressing.
Mix vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise.
Pour over salad and blend.
Refrigerate to blend flavors.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients once. Sift again into 8 or 9-inch square cake pan. Make 3 wells in flour mixture. In first, put vinegar. In second, put oil. In third, put vanilla. Pour water over all ingredients. Stir until mixed well. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Ice cake in pan.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake until brown in a 300° oven, then continue baking for 40 minutes in a 200° oven.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a frying pan; add onions and cook until tender. Add broccoli, soup, cheese and cooked rice.
Simmer until warm. (If mixture seems thick, add a little milk.)
Place in
a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6. Enjoy!

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer broccoli, then the chicken (deboned).
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hocus pocus rolls
directions: Separate the crescent rolls in triangles.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Dip a marshmallow into the butter, roll it in the sugar mix and place it in
a triangle.
Pinch the dough together around the marshmallow and seal edges. Dip top of each roll in butter and then into the sugar mix.
Bake in greased muffin cups for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Preheat Oven 375° Mix shortening, sugar, brown sugar, egg and vanilla using electric mixer. Stir in remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoon ont to ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 min. Remove immediately from baking sheet. Will still be a little white when removed but will continue to bake on cooling rack.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Add sweetened condensed milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into prepared crust.
Chill until firm.
Top with fruit, if desired.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix beans, celery and onion in large bowl.
Toss lightly. Drain extra water or juice off.
Add sugar, vinegar and oil in another bowl.
Stir well.
Add all ingredients together.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: twice baked spaghetti
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Boil and drain spaghetti according to package.
Mix and place spaghetti, sauce and beef in a 9 x 12-inch rectangle baking dish.
Place sliced or shredded Mozzarella cheese on top.
Place in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is lightly browned.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: tandy kakes
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla, baking powder and salt.
Then add milk and butter.
Pour into greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While hot, spread with peanut butter.
Refrigerate until cold.
Melt Hershey bar.
Spread over top.
Refrigerate at least 1/2 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: caramels
directions: Mix all together and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Stir all the time.
Take off of stove and add 1 cup of pecans that have been cut up.
Pour contents into a well-greased pan.
Let cool and cut into squares and wrap in wax paper.

title: apple meringue pudding
directions: None of the ingredients needs to be exact!
Sponge cake may be used in place of Swiss roll.
Slice Swiss roll and arrange in base of a 2 pint souffle dish.
Spoon over rind and juice of lemon. Spread apple on top.
Whisk egg whites until stiff and whisk in 1/2 of sugar until meringue is stiff again.
Pile on top of apple and make peaks.
Dredge with remaining sugar.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch cake pan in order listed.
Do not mix it up!!!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Amazing, but it works!

title: christmas choir punch
directions: Pour fruit juices into percolator.
Place remaining ingredients in basket of percolator.
Perk and enjoy!

title: mexican poor man dessert(also known as capitutada)
directions: Take day-old French bread and slice in 4 x 4-inch squares. Lightly brown two sides of bread in small amount of oil; add more oil, if needed.
Place each slice in layer form.
Place in Pyrex or baking dish large enough to fit bread squares.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken; save chicken broth and pull chicken from the bone.
Saute next 4 ingredients.
Add tomatoes, pimentos, soups, cheese and chicken.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add cooked spaghetti to other ingredients.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Combine rhubarb, salt and sugar; let stand in cool place overnight.
Boil mixture for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and stir in gelatin, mixing well, until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into jars and seal with paraffin.

title: rhubarb surprise pie
directions: Arrange rhubarb in unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with jello. Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle on top of pie.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until rhubarb is tender and crust is brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together in loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for about an hour, stirring every so often.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken on lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine; stir well and spoon evenly over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix and dribble butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter dessert
directions: Combine peanuts, flour and butter.
Press into the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer in order listed.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with white corn chips.

title: marinade for steaks or chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Soak meat all day or overnight in marinade.

title: frozen peach daiquiri
directions: Cut frozen peaches into chunks and put into blender or food processor, then add the water, rum and daiquiri mix.
Blend at high speed until smooth.
Makes 4 "normal" drinks.
Frozen peaches are preferred as then no ice or ice cubes are needed in the drink.
Serve with jalapeno dip and chips.

title: swedish butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix thoroughly. Press through a cookie press on a lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wyatt cafeteria baked eggplant
directions: Cut peeled eggplant into 1-inch cubes and soak in salt water in refrigerator overnight or minimum of 6 hours.
Drain eggplant and place in pan.
Cover with water and simmer until tender.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or quiche dish. Top with pizza sauce, 1/2 cup chopped pepperoni, black olives, green pepper, onion or whatever you prefer.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove and top with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 5 minutes more.

title: kiss cake
directions: Cream together the butter or margarine, vanilla, sugar and salt.
To creamed mixture, add eggs, date mixture, flour and chopped walnuts.
Mix and stir in Hershey's Kisses.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan.
Cake will not rise in pan.
Cool.

title: frozen rhubarb preserves
directions: Mix rhubarb, sugar and pineapple in pan.
Bring to boil.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in jello.
Place in container and freeze.

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: milk gravy
directions: Heat shortening in iron skillet and brown flour, salt and seasoned salt until medium brown.
Add milk and stir, cooking until desired consistency.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine peppers, corn meal mix, onion, corn, cheese, onion, oil and milk; mix.
Add the beaten eggs last.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 450° for 35 to 45 minutes. Bread will be moist.
Cut into small squares and freeze, if desired.

title: mulligan stew(30 minute meal)
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain and add tomato sauce, pork and beans and salt and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes on low heat until thickened.
Serve with cornbread.
Serves 4.

title: mexican chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of a 9 x 7-inch pan.
Top with a can of chili.
Top with cheese and olives.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy dream salad
directions: Stir dry ingredients into cottage cheese.
Mix well with rest of ingredients.
Simple and delicious.

title: pineapple-orange punch
directions: Place sherbet in large punch bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Yields 5 quarts (orange color).

title: orange cheesecake
directions: Combine the crumbs with 3 tablespoons of melted butter and 3 tablespoons of sugar.
Press into the bottom of an ungreased 8 1/2-inch spring-form pan.

title: grandma allen's drop cookies
directions: Drop onto pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat caramels in double boiler until sauce is smooth.
Mix beaten eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla together and add to caramel sauce.
Add pecans.
Put in unbaked pie shell and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a cast-iron pan.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour into pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Add blueberries or apples slightly cooked with sugar.
Pour on top.

title: peanut butter cups cookies
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices. Then cut slices into 2 even portions. Spray mini muffin tin with nonstick cooking spray. Place cut portions into each cup. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Unwrap all of the Reese's mini peanut butter cups. As soon as cookies come out of the oven, place 1 peanut butter cup into each muffin hole. Push down gently until top of peanut butter cups is even with cookie. Let cool about 5 minutes, then run a knife around each cookie and they should pop out.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Put 2 cubes margarine, 4 tablespoons cocoa and 1 cup milk in saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Mix together in large bowl the flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Pour chocolate mixture over flour mixture; beat well.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs; beat again.
Bake in large cookie sheet (jelly roll pan) at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix milk and pudding for 2 minutes. Blend in Cool Whip. Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with honey graham cracker squares. Put half mixture on top of crackers, then put another layer of crackers and other half of mixture.

title: easter casserole(breakfast)
directions: Brown sausage, onion and pepper in skillet; drain.

title: taco bean soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Cook about 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve in bowls with crushed tortilla chips, grated cheese and shredded lettuce on top.

title: peach gelatin salad
directions: Bring to boil the first 3 ingredients; remove from heat.
Add peach jello.
Refrigerate until it begins to jell.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Add to slightly jelled mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: veggie salad
directions: Cut all ingredients in bite-size pieces.
Mix dressings, oil and vinegar.
Let set for 20 minutes.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.

title: krum kakes
directions: Cream all ingredients together. Drop 1 tablespoon of batter into center of heated cake iron. Bake, turn and roll into shape.

title: peanut butter and chocolate chip squares
directions: Cream the butter, brown sugar, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Combine chocolate chips and peanut butter chips; stir into batter.
Spread mixture evenly into greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pan.
Cut into bars.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: normandy pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in hot oil, about 2 minutes for each side.
Place in ovenproof dish with lid; keep warm.

title: no fat banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a loaf pan (sprayed with cooking spray).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: everyone comes to my house for iced tea
directions: Boil 1 quart of bottled or filtered water in a pan on stovetop.
Add two large Lipton tea bags, cover pan and remove from light.
Let steep for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in an oblong pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: blueberry buttermilk muffins
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and eggs together until smooth.
Add milk and soda mixture and beat well.
Add flour and mix until smooth.
Add blueberries.
Pour into greased muffin tins, 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until brown on top.

title: tarragon orange sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine all sauce ingredients; blend well. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes, until sauce is thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear.
Garnish with additional mandarin oranges and fresh tarragon, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill overnight or longer.

title: sauerkraut and spaetzle(germany)
directions: Make spaetzle by mixing eggs, water, salt and enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Roll out, lay on a plate and then, holding the plate over a kettle of boiling water on the stove, cut the dough in odd sized pieces, like very heavy noodles.
Skim out, drain and season with bread crumbs browned in melted butter.
Cook sauerkraut and serve with spaetzle.

title: complete chicken dinner
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put cream of chicken soup over chicken.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together, beating after each egg. Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Turn out on plate and brush with glaze made from lemonade and sugar.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat all together and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: jumbo oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Add dry ingredients and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hurry up rolls
directions: Whip up all together til nice 'n smooth.
Drop sum nuts 'r blueberries, etc. in iffn they suit yo fancy...spoon in greasy muffin tins 'n bake at 400°
fur 'bout 10 minutes.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken pieces in hot oil.
Remove and drain on brown paper.
Saute onions, garlic, mushrooms and peppers in remaining oil until soft.
Add tomato sauce and spices.
Add chicken and simmer 30 minutes.
Boil spaghetti noodles, drain and put in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over noodles, top with cheese and melt under broiler if serving immediately.
Can be reheated.

title: coconut rice
directions: Open the coconut and shred the coconut meat inside.
Drain the coconut, but keep the coconut milk.
Put the coconut milk in a saucepan and heat it to boiling until it becomes dark.
(This is called titote.)
Add the sugar until the titote turns golden.
Add the 4 cups of water with the raisins and let the mixture boil for 20 minutes.
Add salt (to taste) and the rice and cook until almost dry, about 20 minutes.
Add the butter and stir.
Cover and let simmer for awhile on low heat.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: no-bake corn flake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and Karo in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add peanut butter
and
corn
flakes
or Cheerios. Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls on
a
cookie sheet to cool.

title: duck creole
directions: Season ducks with Creole seasoning inside and out.
Fill cavity of ducks with mixture of green onions, celery and bell peppers.
Brown ducks in fat, then add chicken broth and cooking sherry.
Cook until tender, debone ducks and add mushrooms.
Serve over rice.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets and pineapple and add juices to remaining ingredients, except jello.
Bring juices, water, vinegar, sugar and lemon juice to boil.
Remove from stove.
Add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add beets and pineapple.
Pour into mold or 7 x 11-inch Pyrex pan.
Cut into squares.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: mother's raisin filled cookies
directions: *Sour milk equals 1 cup milk plus 1 tablespoon vinegar.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine popcorn, peanuts and M&M's.
Melt together butter, oil and marshmallows.
Mix all ingredients together.
Butter tube pan. Press mixture in pan and refrigerate 1 hour.
Remove from pan and slice while cold.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Combine oil, eggs and sugar in a large bowl.
Use electric mixer and mix well. Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, stirring just until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries.

title: hot salad
directions: Make a green salad.
Rinse and drain Ranch Style beans, then add to salad.
Crunch up Fritos and add to salad just before serving.
Use Catalina dressing.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and roll to size of buckeyes (1-inch). Chill.
Melt chocolate in double boiler with paraffin.

title: italian venison roast
directions: Marinate roast with Italian dressing, turning occasionally and make sure it stays moist.
Next day, place roast in oven cooking bag and add potatoes, carrots, onion, salt and pepper to taste. Add 1/4 cup Italian dressing mixed with 1/4 cup water.
Close bag and cook according to directions on box or any any other roast cooked in oven bag.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Mix in oleo, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Put into casserole and top with toasted bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: italian bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook carrots, celery and onion in hot olive oil about 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in water, cabbage, lentils, tomato puree, sugar, salt, oregano and pepper. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until lentils are very soft.
Ladle into bowls.
Makes 5 main-dish servings.

title: stir-fry broccoli
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Set aside.
Trim off outer leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends of stalks. Wash broccoli in cold water.
Cut stalks diagonally into 1-inch thick slices.
Cut flowerets into 1-inch pieces.
Pour oil around top of preheated wok, coating sides.
Allow to heat at medium high (325°) for 2 minutes.
Add broccoli; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add onion; stir-fry 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce mixture; cover and reduce heat to low (225°).
Cook 5 minutes, or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spoon bread
directions: Cook corn meal in milk until mixture is of the consistency of thick cream. Beat in one at a time the egg yolks. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Turn into a greased baking dish and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: In large bowl, mix first three ingredients.
Add flour and baking powder.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Mix sugars, soda and milk in saucepan.
Bring to boil, lower heat and cook until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until creamy.
Drop rapidly from a spoon onto waxed paper or an oiled platter to form patties.
If mixture becomes too stiff, place pan in hot water for little while.
Makes about 1 dozen pralines.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and mix.
Add oil, vanilla, then add zucchini, salt, baking powder, baking soda and flour. Add pineapple and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: california chicken sandwich
directions: Pierce chicken with fork several times.
Place in resealable bag.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight. Grill or broil chicken breasts 7 to 10 minutes or until done.
Layer a chicken breast, 2 cheese slices, 1 chili, 1 or 2 orange slices and a lettuce leaf on each bun. Serve with bread and butter pickles and tortilla chips.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: mexican hot chocolate
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in small saucepan; stir in water. Bring to boil; reduce heat and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add cloves, cinnamon and milk.
Simmer 5 minutes (do not boil).
Whisk in vanilla.
Pour hot chocolate into mugs; top with whipped cream.
Use cinnamon sticks for stirrers.
Yield: 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add sugar and baking powder to yeast.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Scald milk; add margarine, sugar and salt.
Cool, then add eggs.
Combine all with 4 1/2 cups flour.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 2 hours before serving.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
(Shape as butterhorns or pinwheels in muffin pans.)

title: lime punch
directions: Mix lime jello, water and sugar.
Boil until dissolved.
Add juices and vanilla.
Finish gallon with water.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Note: Do not substitute margarine for butter.

title: cream cheese filling
directions: Place cream cheese and butter over low heat.
Let melt and add powdered sugar (by sifting).
Add flavoring and nuts.

title: cocoons
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Cream butter.
Sift flour; add sugar, butter and vanilla.
Mix and add nuts.
Mix well.
Pinch off tiny pieces and bake on ungreased baking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: rice pudding
directions: Melt oleo.
Mix in sugar and eggs; pour over rice in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: fluffy lemon berry pie
directions: Cream the cheese in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth. Gradually beat in milk until well blended. Add pudding mixes. Beat 2 minutes or until smooth. Immediately stir in 1/2 of the whipped topping. Spoon into crust. Top with remaining whipped topping. Refrigerate for 3 hours or until set. Garnish with berries.

title: scotches
directions: Butter bottom of pan.
Melt butter in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and blend.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Mix thoroughly. Add nuts and stir lightly to combine.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and squash.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes two 9 x 5 inch loaves.

title: quick and easy chicken pie
directions: Cook
chicken
in
2-quarts
water.
When
done, remove chicken and let cool.
Set aside cup of broth.
Debone chicken and place
in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Combine can of cream of celery
soup
and
broth.
Heat
over
low
heat until well mixed. Pour
over
chicken.
Melt
butter in saucepan and add milk.
Mix in flour.
Mix well.
Spoon this over chicken until well coated. Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 40 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Let cool for 15 minutes.

title: working girl pie
directions: Mix and pour into crust.
Top with can of cherry pie filling and Cool Whip.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend all the ingredients together until smooth.
This dip is very good with fresh raw vegetables, chips and excellent as a topping on baked potatoes.

title: tomato banana surprise
directions: In quart jar mix onion, vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar. Refrigerate.
Just before serving, combine tomatoes and bananas. Pour dressing over all and toss.
Try it to believe it!

title: tuna balls
directions: Drain
tuna and save liquid and pour over bread to soak. Mix other
ingredients and bread crumbs.
Make tiny balls; dip each in
Pet
milk
and
roll
in
corn flake crumbs.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve on toothpick.
After cooking, these may be frozen.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice all the vegetables.
I
use whatever I have in my refrigerator.
Use a wok or Teflon frypan.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place raisins and/or nuts on bottom.
Place frozen dinner rolls around pan.
Sprinkle 1 cup brown sugar over rolls. Sprinkle melted butter over rolls.
Sprinkle dry pudding over rolls.
Mix together remaining brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Cover with damp towel.
Place in unheated oven on lowest rack overnight.
When ready to bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mother's fruit salad
directions: Drain off pineapple juice and save 1/4 cup, adding lemon juice, sugar and salt to this and set aside.
Spread pineapple out onto paper towels in a pie plate.
Quarter, core and chop apples, leaving peel on, and put into a large bowl; toss with juice (will keep from turning dark) and let stand while you prepare rest of the fruit.
Peel and slice bananas into the apple mixture, tossing gently.
Drain off excess juice.
Using a wooden spoon (won't mash bananas), gently stir all ingredients together.
Chill 30 minutes, gently toss again; sprinkle a few pecan pieces and a little coconut on top and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Break vermicelli; cook and drain.
Combine with first 7 ingredients.
Use amount of milk to give desired moistness.
Bake at 300°
for 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes or paprika.
Serve.

title: angel cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well with wire whisk.
Pour into 10-inch iron skillet sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Delicious!

title: spaghetti lasagne
directions: 1st Layer:
12 ounces cooked spaghetti, 2 tablespoons margarine and 1/4 cup grated Parmesan cheese.

title: crisp chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine.
Mix together corn meal, flour, paprika, pepper and salt.
Dip each piece of chicken in melted margarine, then dip in corn meal mixture.
Arrange chicken in a baking pan and bake for about 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sugar cured meat(for a 200 pound hog)
directions: Mix all well together.
This is for one joint of meat and use more according to weight of hog.
Sprinkle mixture on clean white cloth large enough to wrap joint of meat; place joint on mixture and generously apply all over to joint, making sure to coat heavily around bones.
Wrap in cloth, tying tightly, place in clean sack; hang with bone end down.

title: majestic spinach salad
directions: In 2-quart bowl, layer Swiss cheese, spinach, eggs and mushrooms.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, milk, lemon juice and sugar, mixing until well blended.
Stir in green onion. Spread over salad to seal.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Top with bacon before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sue frances gander's florentine manicotti
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Melt margarine in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Combine ground beef, onion mixture, cooked spinach, cheese, beaten eggs, lemon juice and seasonings in a bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon meat mixture into cooked manicotti shells.
Place shells in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Pour spaghetti sauce on top.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: pink cottage cheese salad
directions: Heat pineapple in juice.
Add strawberry jello and let cool. Add to other ingredients.
Put in serving dish.
Chill.

title: tomato - macaroni salad
directions: Cook the shells according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together and add to cooked shells.
Refrigerate until cool.

title: pork chops and sauce
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops and brown on both sides.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over pork chops.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken curry cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least 2 hours.
Shape into a ball and coat with chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers. Makes one cheese ball.
(Also makes a good sandwich filling if there are leftovers.)

title: quick cocoa cake("spare tire" cake)
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sift all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Do not stir until all ingredients are in bowl.
Beat well about 4 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or similar type pan.
Frost with buttercream icing.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: In a large saucepan, combine apples, sugar, sweetener, water, cinnamon and cloves.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, 10 to 15 minutes or until apples are soft, but still chunky.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 8 (1/2 cup) servings with 115 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make yellow cake as directed on box (2 layers).

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: In a large pot, cook diced potatoes in water until done.
Fry bacon in skillet.
Drain.

title: cracker pie
directions: Mix and bring to rolling boil.
Add 16 soda crackers, broken in quarters.
Do not stir.
Cover with juice.
Boil 8 minutes.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes at 400.

title: meat and rice dish
directions: In large baking dish, add Minute rice, onion soup mix, cream of mushroom soup and water; mix well together.
Place meat of your choice on top of rice mixture.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lime gelatin salad
directions: Mix dry jello into cottage cheese.
Drain pineapple, very dry, and add to mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: dive in potato dippers
directions: You will need Reynolds plastic wrap and Reynolds Cut Rite wax paper.
In a small bowl, combine yogurt and dip mix.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate.
Cut each potato lengthwise into 6 wedges.
On a large microwave-safe plate, arrange potato wedges in circle.
Brush potato wedges with butter; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Rotate plate 1/2 turn. Microwave additional 7 to 9 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Remove wax paper.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes.
Let stand until cheese is melted.
Serve with prepared party dip.
Refrigerate leftover dip.
Serve with raw vegetables or chips.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli and onion; toss lightly. Combine vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise and salt and pour over vegetables.
Toss and let stand.

title: french meat pie
directions: Brown meat, onion and celery; mix in poultry seasoning.
Heat water.
Add bouillon cube; mix until melted.
Break bread into water.
Add to meat mixture.
A large can of whole potatoes, chopped small, can be added.
Simmer on low (electric frypan, if you have one) for about 2 hours.

title: lean and tasty quick chili
directions: You will need a removable crock-pot crock.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in saucepan over medium heat to a boil; boil 15 minutes (don't stir once it starts to boil).
After boiling, remove from heat and put pan in sink in 2-inches deep of cold water.
Beat by hand, adding butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Spread into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: rhubarb coffee cake
directions: Cream together 1 cup white sugar, brown sugar and shortening. Add the egg.
Add alternately sour milk, flour and soda.
Stir in the rhubarb.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar mixed with cinnamon over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: cucumber tea sandwiches
directions: Soak cucumbers and onions overnight in vinegar, salt and pepper.
Soften cream cheese and mix with mayonnaise.
Add 2 to 3 teaspoons vinegar to mixture.
Spread bread with mayonnaise. Spread cream cheese mixture over mayonnaise.
Put a slice of cucumber on 4 corners of slice of bread.
Add slivers of onion on top of each 2 pieces of cucumber.
Sprinkle on a dash of salt and cover with other piece of bread.
Cover with damp tea towel until ready to serve.
Cut into quarters.

title: corn casserole(serves 10)
directions: Melt butter in a medium size casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients in dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: burgundy pot roast
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven or skillet using no fat.
Add garlic, tomato sauce, wine, orange slice, celery, parsley and thyme. Season with salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer gently about 4 hours on stove top or bake at 325° for 4 hours.
Turn meat occasionally, adding water if necessary.
Add onions last 20 minutes of cooking time.
Transfer meat to hot platter and slice. Season gravy to taste and serve with meat.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Add milk, egg and butter.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
The batter will be lumpy.
Do not overbeat.
Stir in blueberries gently.
Spoon batter into greased or papered muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until tops spring back when touched lightly.
Serve warm.

title: heavenly fudge
directions: Bring
sugar,
butter
and milk to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes. Add Hershey bar, Marshmallow Creme and chocolate chips. Beat well;
add nuts.
Pour into large buttered cookie sheet. Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (save 1 cup grated cheese to sprinkle on top) and put in large greased casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: super pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly in medium-sized bowl.
Stir in apple butter, pumpkin, brown sugar, salt, spice and milk, blending well. Pour into pastry shell and bake in preheated oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Continue baking at 350° until filling is set (about 45 minutes).

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Combine all remaining ingredients. I add a little more milk if needed for softness.
Spoon onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until the cookies are golden brown.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: In a large jar, mix garlic, oregano, salt, pepper, olive oil and red wine vinegar.
Shake well to blend.
Place mushrooms and onions in a large bowl.
Pour marinade mixture over mushrooms and onions. Stir to coat. Cover bowl and marinate in refrigerator for at least 3 days, stirring occasionally.

title: luau punch
directions: Shake to blend and serve over ice or blend with ice for a frozen drink.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until done.

title: peanut scotchies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in a large saucepan. Stir in peanut butter. Fold in corn flakes until well coated. Drop by teaspoons onto a serving tray. Refrigerate.

title: green bean and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook beans and broccoli according to package.
Drain.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Pour over vegetables. Top with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, oil and eggs.
Blend well.
Add red coloring, buttermilk, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add 1 cup flour, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add last cup of flour and mix for about 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cake springs back.
Combine milk and sugar.
Pour over hot cake.
Cool before frosting with the Red Velvet Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: fresh strawberry icing
directions: Blend until fluffy and good spreading consistency.
Add additional crushed berries if icing appears too thick.

title: asparagus chicken
directions: Flatten out chicken breasts with a mallet or bottle; salt and pepper them.
Spread cheese over each.
Place 4 to 5 asparagus spears on each breast.
Roll up, fastening with toothpicks. Spray a casserole dish with Pam, then place breasts in it.
Mix together water and soup; pour over breasts.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal. Combine egg and milk. Mix well and stir in flour mixture until just moistened. Chill 24 hours.

title: dill pickles to can
directions: Boil together 10 minutes.
Wash pickles.
Let stand in salt water 10 minutes.
Fill each can with dill seed and grape leaves. (I usually use two; I use a whole stem top of dill seed.)
Put pickles in cans.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over pickles.
Put a small piece or alum in each can and a small chunk of garlic if you like.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and mix well. Pour 1/2 batter into greased 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle cheese evenly and top with remainder of batter. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix together well first 4 ingredients; set aside.
Slice cookie dough rolls into 1/3-inch slices.
Place slices of one roll into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; press together to cover any holes. Spoon in cream cheese mixture evenly and top with slices of remaining package of cookie dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown and center is slightly firm.
Let cool then refrigerate.
Cut into squares.
Serve with chocolate sauce or whipped topping.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 2 1/2 to 3 quart casserole. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit ice
directions: Juice oranges and lemons.
Mix well with mashed bananas and sugar, then freeze.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni dinner as directed on box.
Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into a bowl lined with lettuce (optional).
Can be eaten hot or cold.

title: chicken-a-la-can-can
directions: Mix everything together in a large skillet.
Bring to boil, stirring frequently.
Ready in minutes.
If too thick, just add more milk.
Serve hot over chow mein noodles.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Lay slices of bell pepper on top.

title: beef stew(delicious)
directions: Place the first 4 ingredients in a large casserole and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 5 hours at 275°.
Serves 8.

title: instant pudding chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugars, vanilla and pudding mix in a large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy, then beat in eggs.
Mix flour and soda and gradually add into butter mixture.
Stir in chips. Batter will be stiff.
Drop by rounded teaspoons about 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: In the top of a double boiler, put first 3 ingredients.
Heat until liquid.
Take off stove and add the vanilla.
Dip the strawberries and set them on wax paper until chocolate is hardened.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pretzel delight
directions: Melt butter in square pan.
Add pretzels and 1/2 cup sugar and press to bottom of pan.
Mix Cool Whip, 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese and spread into pan.
Cook juice, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch, just to heat up.
Add pineapple and spread on top. Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat mixture.
Bake in uncooked pie crust at 300°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together.
Put into baking dish and bake in 350° oven until bubbly and brown around edges.
Garnish with small green olives or parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: ruggiero italian salad
directions: The night before serving, combine in small covered bowl the drained pineapple chunks and miniature marshmallows.
Refrigerate. In small pan, combine egg, sugar, pineapple juice and flour. Boil 3 to 5 minutes until thickened.
Put in covered bowl and refrigerate overnight.

title: crepes with crab meat and cheese sauce
directions: Melt margarine.
Add chopped onion and cook until onions are tender.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco, parsley and crab meat.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Prepare crepes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir in 1 cup Wesson oil; add dry ingredients, which have been sifted together.
Add 4 cups finely chopped apples.
This will probably be a very stiff dough.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Frost with coconut pecan frosting.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix as directed on box.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch rectangular pan.
When cake is finished baking, use a fork and make fork holes all over cake.
Mix jello with 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Pour jello mix all over cake while cake is hot. When cake is cool, ice with Cool Whip and top with strawberries.

title: texas chili
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onions.
Drain excess fat.
Add seasonings and stir well.
Add tomato sauce, water and pinto beans; stir well.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature.
Take a fork, mash and stir.
Mix in the dry Ranch salad dressing mix thoroughly.
Mix in shredded cheese.
(You can use 1 to 2 cups of cheese, as much as you like.)
Mix well.
Form into logs or balls.

title: fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and marshmallow cream in mixing bowl until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Makes 3 cups.

title: easy-cheesy-best macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook macaroni or pasta in boiling water until tender, but firm to bite.
Drain and return to saucepan.
Stir in butter and egg.
In large bowl, combine mustard, salt and nutmeg with the tablespoon of boiling water.
Stir in milk, 2 1/2 cups cheese, onion and macaroni or pasta.
Pour macaroni mixture into casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 1 hour or until well browned top crust has formed.

title: sherry's potato casserole
directions: Wash, de-eye potatoes, leave on skins and boil until done. Rinse with cold water and cool.
Grate potatoes.
In same bowl, add sour cream, butter, bacon bits, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Pour mixture into 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle more bacon bits and cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven until brown as desired.

title: hot wings
directions: Cut each chicken wing at the joint, discarding wing tip. Place in large bowl; mix together sauce and oil.
Pour over chicken wings and mix to coat well.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Place wings in single layer in large baking pan and sprinkle with pepper.
Bake in hot 425° oven.
Turn frequently with spatula for even browning.

title: sin
directions: First layer:
Mix flour, pecans and margarine and pack in bottom of pyrex dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: oven fried fish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash, drain and pat fish dry with paper towel.
Lightly oil both sides of fish.
Thoroughly coat both sides of fish with mixture of bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake fish about 30 minutes.
Serve with sprinkles of malt vinegar.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Mix hamburger meat with beans.
Mix tomatoes and soup together.
Start with 3 or 4 shells in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add or cover shells with 1/2 meat mixture, then soup mixture and top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Repeat with shells and mixtures.
Add Cheddar cheese on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This is my grandkids favorite.

title: yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Add stick of oleo to rice while still warm.
Add Mexicorn and cream of mushroom soup to rice mixture.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Simmer ingredients together for 30 or more minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and evaporated milk in pot.
Cook to form ball, then add vanilla and nuts.
Spoon out onto wax paper.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dates, raisins and nuts.
Form into rolls and store in refrigerator or freezer at least overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake as needed.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak crumbs in milk and add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Cover with tomato catsup.
Bake in loaf pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Top each loaf with 1 teaspoon melted margarine or butter.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Add all ingredients together in a saucepan. Heat until sugar dissolves.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add oatmeal. Stir.
Drop on waxed paper and cool.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add flour; mix, then add oatmeal and mix.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet. Cook 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.
Do not overcook.
Cool and spread Betty Crocker vanilla frosting between 2 cookies.
Store in airtight container.

title: sausage balls
directions: Put sausage into large bowl.
Add Bisquick and cheese; mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
May be frozen for later use.

title: beanie wieners
directions: In a skillet, brown sliced up hot dogs with 1 teaspoon of shortening.
Add pork and beans, ketchup, water and salt; simmer for 10 minutes.
Yield: 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: stir-fry green pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 1/8-inch pieces.
Combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Add beef.
Toss and set aside while preparing vegetables. Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
Add beef and toss until browned.
Taste meat.
If not tender, cover and cook 30 minutes on low heat.
Turn to medium heat.
Add vegetables.
Cook 20 minutes. Mix water with cornstarch.
Add to pan.
Stir and cook until thick.
Add tomatoes or pimentos and heat.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: raisin cake
directions: Combine raisins and water. Bring to boil. Remove from heat. Stir in oil. Cool. Stir in sugar and egg. Sift dry ingredients. Beat into raisin mixture. Stir in nuts. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool and cut into bars.

title: apple butter cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream sugar and butter or margarine.
Beat in egg, oats and apple butter.
Combine dry ingredients, gradually adding to the creamed mixture, along with the milk.
Beat until blended.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Chill, then drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Yield:
2 1/2 dozen.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle meat, onion and cheese evenly over bottom.
Mix together the remaining ingredients, pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes, let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix together Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet or pan.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix butter and garlic together; brush on warm biscuits.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix per box instructions.
If strawberries are frozen, thaw thoroughly.
Prepare instant pudding per box instructions.
In a very large bowl or punch bowl, layer the cake, strawberries, pudding, pineapple and cool whip.
Repeat.

title: sinful salad
directions: Mix fruit and drained chestnuts. Dissolve jello in water. Mix with fruit. Pour 1/2 of mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate 1 hour, then spread yogurt over all. Put other 1/2 of jello on top. Refrigerate. Makes 16 servings.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix flour and margarine until crumbly; add pecans.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown, then cool.

title: caramelized cake squares
directions: In saucepan, combine butter and sugar over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Bring to boil and cook until syrup reaches soft ball stage (234° to 240°).
Remove from heat.
Using tongs, dip cake cubes in syrup; roll in pecans.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Before serving, cover with cocktail sauce.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In large bowl, mix pudding and whipped topping.
Add pineapple, nuts and marshmallows.
Chill.

title: maurice's pound cake
directions: Beat the cream cheese, sugar, and Crisco at high speed with mixer.
Add 5 eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining ingredients, beating until smooth.
Pour into greased bundt or
tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes (check for doneness at 1 hour and 20 minutes).

title: mincemeat cake
directions: Generously grease and flour tubular cake pan.
Combine sugar and mincemeat; mix well.
Add 2 cups flour and 1 cup buttermilk. Mix well again.
Add remaining flour and milk; mix well.
Pour into cake pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Remove from oven, letting cool for about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Remaining cake can be frozen.

title: lemon ice
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes; cool.
Add lemon juice; place in freezer tray.
Freeze.
Serve scraped ice in sherbet glasses, topped with pineapple chunks, strawberries, bananas or oranges.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and canned milk to boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Add nuts and vanilla; beat well. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes approximately 3 pounds.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix peanut butter and sugar. Add egg and soda. Chill dough. Form into 1 1/2-inch rolls. Cut into slim slices and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Crisscross with water dipped fork. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cauliflower and carrot casserole
directions: Parboil
cauliflower
and
carrots for several minutes. Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Slice carrots into 1/4 inch slices. Put
vegetables into casserole and pour soup and milk on
top. Melt
butter or margarine in frypan.
Crush crackers and
stir into
the
butter or margarine to coat.
Coat well. Put
cracker mixture on top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: easy beef stew
directions: In electric skillet, brown meat in oil. Add sauce and water. Simmer 2 hours.
In the last 30 minutes, add vegetables and seasoning.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream
butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients
together
and
blend
into
creamed
mixture. Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours, after making into 2 rolls.
Cut thin slices;
flatten with glass.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: old fashioned biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Blend in shortening; add milk.
Work lightly.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick; cut out.
Bake in a well greased pan until brown at 400°.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs to butter mixture, one at a time, beating after each is added, sifting dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with milk, then vanilla.
Pour into prepared layer pans.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.

title: butter crunch
directions: Butter baking sheet.
Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add sugar; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in water and corn syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to 290° on candy thermometer.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with Doritos.
Spread chicken over chips. Mix soups together and pour over chicken and chips.
Pour tomatoes on top.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix with
hands;
shape into small balls and bake on an ungreased cookie
sheet at 300° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.
Can be frozen in Ziploc bags.

title: oyster stew
directions: Drain oyster and reserve juice; set aside oysters and juice. In a large sauce pot, heat butter over medium heat. Add onion and celery; cook until soft. Do not brown. Add milk, cream, salt, peppers and oyster juice. Bring to a mild boil and cook 5 minutes. Add oysters and cook until edges curl, about 3 to 4 minutes. Garnish with paprika, oyster crackers and hot sauce to taste.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and light colored.
Add sugar gradually, continue to beat.
Blend in vanilla.
Heat milk and butter until scalding.
Beat into egg mixture quickly.
Add dry ingredients a little at a time, mixing well.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stir-fried chicken with broccoli and peanuts
directions: In a wok, heat 2 tablespoons oil over high heat until hot, swirling to coat sides of pan.
Add broccoli, carrots, celery, scallions, garlic and ginger; stir-fry until crisp-tender, 4 to 6 minutes.
Remove to bowl.

title: green chile brownies
directions: Mix Ortega diced green chilies into your favorite brownie mix.

title: children's fudgsicle
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into freezer pop molds and freeze.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mock peanut brittle
directions: Bring corn syrup and sugar to boil.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes and stir until coated. Spread on waxed paper and let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except cider.
Boil 1 hour.
Add cider and heat thoroughly.
Strain before serving.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Heat water. Open jello into large bowl. Pour water over jello. Mix well. Add cranberry juice cocktail and applesauce. Let it set awhile, but not long enough to gel. Add lemon juice. Lightly grease a Pyrex dish and add mixture. Refrigerate until firm.

title: key lime pie
directions: Squeeze lime into condensed milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill until set.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, condensed milk and lemon juice; beat until creamy.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into crust and chill for 2 hours before serving.
Serves 6.

title: one day pickles
directions: Put
slice
of
homemade
bread
on bottom of container (best is
plastic).
Put
cucumber
slices, onion, garlic and dill
on top of bread.
Top with another slice of bread.
Pour hot
brine of water, vinegar, sugar and salt over the cucumber mixture. Cover
and let stand for a day.
Place in refrigerator.
You can eat them after a day.

title: glo's sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Sift flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; set aside.
Mix butter, confectioners sugar, egg, vanilla and almond extract in a large bowl.
Blend in flour mixture.
Cover and chill 2 to 3 hours. Divide dough in half and roll each half 2/16-inch thick on a lightly floured board.
Dip a cookie cutter into flour and press on dough to make various designs.
Sprinkle with colored sugar or granulated sugar.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes or until light brown on edges.
Cool on cooling rack. Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: low-fat banana muffins
directions: In a bowl, chop bananas.
Add milk, sweetener, vanilla and water.
Mix well.
Over this, sprinkle flour, then baking soda. Stir this into liquid and spoon into muffin tins.
Makes 11 to 12 muffins.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and save broth. Cook spaghetti in broth. Dice cooked chicken and set aside. Saute in 1 cup chicken broth, the stick of butter, Ro-Tel, mushrooms and chopped onion. Add diced chicken. Drain spaghetti and add chicken mixture. Pour all in casserole dish and add cubed or shredded cheese. Bake until hot and bubbly.

title: nana's chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Cover with Swiss cheese slices.
Mix soup and wine together; pour over.
Mix stuffing mix and melted butter together; pour over.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until chicken is cooked.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In a punch bowl, crumble 1/2 of the cake.
Top with 1/2 of the pudding.
Layer with the cherry filling, 1/2 of the Cool Whip, the remainder of cake, pudding and Cool Whip.
Top with coconut and nuts.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding together by hand.
Fold in whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour or more.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk. Gradually add flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add rhubarb and mix just enough to coat it completely with batter. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
(I mix 2 or 3 tablespoons sugar with about 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.)

title: red velvet cake
directions: Add vinegar and soda; cover and set aside.
Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with cocoa and food coloring and add to mixture. Stir salt into buttermilk.
Alternate adding buttermilk and dry ingredients to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Quickly add soda and vinegar to mixture and blend well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Do not overbeat mixture.)
Ice layers with icing of choice.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for only 30 minutes.

title: vanilla sugar
directions: Split bean lengthwise and bury in sugar.
Store this in a glass container and use in coffee, on cereal, or in baking.
The longer the mixture sits, the stronger the sugar will taste of vanilla.

title: ila mae's cobbler
directions: Stir milk, flour and sugar together in a bowl until free of lumps or until smooth.
Melt butter in a deep baking dish.
Pour milk, flour and sugar mixture into melted butter.
Do not stir. Pour fruit into center of this batter mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot with milk or ice cream.
Delicious and perfect every time.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Wash breast and pat dry.
Place in shallow baking dish, skin side up.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Baste with pan drippings occasionally.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stuff into breast cavity.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until chicken is fork-tender.

title: oriental pork wontons
directions: Cook ground pork until no pink remains; drain.
Stir in carrots, water chestnuts, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and ginger root.
Mix well.
Lay out one wonton wrapper at a time and spoon 1 teaspoon of filling onto the center.
Brush edges with water and bring opposite corners together and pinch.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Repeat until filling is gone.
Brush wontons with margarine.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.

title: nancy's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add along with vanilla. Mix together apples and nuts; then add to mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: pizza pie
directions: Combine melted margarine, egg,
and cake mix.
Spread dough onto a large greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350°
for 12 minutes. Let pizza pie crust cool.
Mix powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese and spread over cooled crust.
In the center of the pie pan arrange a small circle of pineapple chunks.
Make a circle around the pineapple with cherry pie filling.
Make a circle around the pie filling with sliced kiwi fruit, then make a final circle around kiwi fruit on the outside edge with sliced peaches.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: flowerpot pie
directions: Pour milk; add pudding and mix.
Stir in whipped topping.
Stir in 1 cup cookie crumbs.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Freeze overnight.
Before serving, let stand 15 minutes.
Garnish with gumdrop flowers, made by flattening gumdrops and cutting with small cutter.
Attach to a pretzel stick and stick in each serving.
Serves 8.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in little lukewarm water to which one tablespoon of sugar has been added and allow to stand while mixing dough.
Scald milk; add sugar and melted shortening.
Pour into large bowl of mixer.
Add eggs and turn to No. 2 speed.
Add 2 cups of flour and continue to beat on No. 1 speed.
Add dissolved yeast.
Beat 4 or 5 minutes on medium speed.
Add another cup or more of flour.
Turn out on floured board and add enough flour to make it stiff enough to knead.
