Knead just enough to shape.
Place in greased bowl and rise until double in bulk.
Knead down well. Cut into two equal parts.
Roll out each piece to the size of a pie or larger.
I usually make the size of a pizza.
Divide into 12 wedges or smaller pieces and roll, starting with the wide end. Place on pan with small end down.
You can brush tops with condensed milk and sprinkle with poppy seed, if desired.
Let rise until doubled in bulk and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
It is good to preheat oven to 425°, then reduce to 375°.

title: chess pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Bake in unbaked shells at
300° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked pork chops with rice
directions: First salt the chops and roll in flour, then brown lightly in small amount of oil or bacon fat in frypan; chops do not have to be thoroughly done at this stage. Then place rice in bottom of lightly buttered baking pan, spreading evenly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together. Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown.

title: soft oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy. Add combined flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Mix well.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Drop by rounded tablespoons on ungreased cookie sheet, 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookie; 10 to 11 minutes for crisp cookie.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Melt morsels in microwave.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
If mixture is too stiff, reheat in microwave.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator until hard.
Cut into squares and enjoy!

title: brown sugar crisp cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugars, margarine, egg, vanilla, allspice and cinnamon until smooth and creamy.
Stir in baking mix and nuts.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.

title: butter rich spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and sifted powdered sugar well.
Add egg and flavorings.
Mix.
Add dry ingredients gradually.
Mix well. Press a small amount of dough through a cookie press onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Choose desired shapes on cookie press. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: raspberry-pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Stir in raspberries until separated.
Add undrained pineapple.
Chill until very thick, then stir to distribute fruits evenly.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Serves 10.

title: potato cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Beat eggs separately.
(Fold in whites after all other things are added.)
Mix all together. Pour into 2 greased and floured Bundt or angel food cake pans or 4 loaf pans.
Bake at 350°.
Cool.
Wrap in foil for several weeks. (Not required, but it tastes wonderful if you do.)

title: hearty bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs, with mayonnaise.
Place on nest of lettuce.
Chill thoroughly.
Garnish with wedge of hard-boiled eggs.

title: johnny a's beans
directions: Prepare 6 squares of heavy-duty doubled foil.
Oil lightly one side.
Core apples and scoop out to make larger cavity.
Combine beans with marmalade and fill apples.
Wrap and seal packages. Place on medium-hot coals for about 30 minutes.

title: fresh cooked collard greens
directions: Cut and wash large handful of fresh collard greens.
In large pot, brown sausage, onion and garlic.
If turkey sausage is used, add olive oil (or other oil) to coat pan and avoid sticking.
As ingredients cook on low heat, cut the greens by first cutting out the thick center stem, then cut the leaves in 1 to 2-inch pieces (small).
Begin adding the cut greens to the cooking sausage mixture.
Let saute just slightly, then add just enough water to prevent any sticking.
Greens should simmer until tender, from 30 minutes to 1 hour.
As they cook, add lemon juice, salt, pepper, small amount of cumin and hot pepper sauce to taste.
Hot pepper sauce is hot peppers in vinegar, canned.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Place chicken evenly into bottom of frying pan. Add 1 cup of water and spray with butter. Sprinkle other ingredients over chicken to cover. Cook on medium heat. After turning chicken, sprinkle spices again. Continue cooking and turning chicken every 5 minutes. Cook until chicken browns.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Heat for a few minutes. Add milk gradually and bring to a boil.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Add enough xxxx sugar until consistency desired.

title: pop-a-pizza
directions: Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons pizza sauce on each muffin.
Place 1 slice pepperoni on sauce. Top with cheese. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: mary's dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, onions and Worcestershire sauce,
Spread on the bottom of a shallow dish (pie tin size).
Pour cocktail sauce over this first layer.
Then spread deviled ham over the cocktail sauce evenly.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over this last layer, if you wish.
Crackers or corn chips are best for dipping.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop green onions and pastrami.
MIx cream cheese, onion and pastrami together.
Form into a ball or log.
Roll in Bac*Os and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: boudin balls
directions: Remove boudin from casing.
Form dressing into balls about the size of walnuts.
Dip balls in beaten egg, then into bread crumbs. Deep fry balls in cooking oil at about 325° until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with toothpicks. Makes 20 to 25.
This is a simple and excellent appetizer or hors d'oeuvre.

title: conglomeration sandwiches
directions: Chop ham slightly, dice cheese into small pieces.
Mix ingredients and add to the ham and cheese.
Spread onto buns. Wrap in foil.
Store in refrigerator overnight or freeze for a later date.
Heat oven to 450°. Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 18 to 20 sandwiches.
Great to keep in the freezer for unexpected company.

title: cherry coffee cake
directions: Stir almond extract into pie filling.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, mix oil, sugar, vanilla, and orange juice.
Add eggs one at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Mix flour and baking powder together, and add gradually to batter.
Put 1/2 the batter into greased 9 inch x 13 inch pan.	Spread cherries over batter. Cover with remaining batter.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Blender is used to blend
cucumbers.
Add other ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Chill.
Serves 4.
Great on a hot summer day with crackers or bread.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir while heating thoroughly on medium heat.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into ice cream mixer until frozen.

title: springtime potato salad
directions: Bring unpeeled new potatoes to a boil and simmer 20 minutes. Drain and cool slightly; peel if desired.
Cut potatoes into 3/4-inch pieces.

title: diabetic prune cookies
directions: Mix together oil, cooked prunes, chopped apples, eggs and sugar.
Add orange rind and mix well.
Add salt, soda, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg, mix well then add flour and mix.
Add nuts, coconut and raisins.
Mix well, take a teaspoon of mixture and drop on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, more or less depending on thickness.
Makes 9 to 10 dozen. These cookies freeze well.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Use as a dip for raw vegetables or potato chips and pretzels.

title: wild berry tart
directions: Preparation time: 25 minutes.
Refrigeration: 30 minutes. Cook: 45 minutes.

title: mounds candy bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Bake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together in saucepan 1 cup sugar, marshmallows and 1 cup milk.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat and add coconut.
Pour this mixture over cake as soon as it comes out of oven.
Let cool.
Place 1/4 cup milk, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup margarine in pan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in chocolate
chips. Top cake with this mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Very rich.

title: cheese chops and rice
directions: Rub chops with fresh grated garlic.
Press bread crumbs into chops.
Brown in butter.
Set aside.
Prepare rice in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
When about 1/2 of water is absorbed, lay browned chops on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover, add shredded cheese over rice and chops.
Cook until cheese is bubbly.
Serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease a large bundt pan.
Cut biscuits into quarters. Combine cinnamon and sugar.
Roll each piece of biscuit in the cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Arrange pieces of biscuits in bundt pan. Melt margarine and brown sugar.
Pour over sugared biscuits. Bake in preheated 350 degree oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool bread 10 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan and serve.

title: microwave chocolate pudding
directions: In large microwavable bowl, combine sugar, cocoa, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Stirring constantly, gradually blend in 1/4 milk until smooth, then remaining milk.
Microwave on High, stirring twice, for 6 minutes or until pudding boils.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon into 4 dessert dishes.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until chilled.
If desired, garnish with bananas.
Contains about 160 calories (180 with banana), 2 g fat and 130 mg sodium.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour, baking powder, cocoa and salt together.
Add to sugar mix, alternating with milk.
Bake in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: jack pot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion and pepper. Cook until well done. Drain fat; add tomato sauce, corn and 1/2 cup cheese. Pour ingredients in a large casserole dish. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: good corn corn bread
directions: Mix just as listed.
Cook in hot skillet in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: crab stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large pot.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Using medium heat, heat until thoroughly hot, stirring occasionally.

title: chocaroon pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in eggs, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs together.
Combine flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to dry ingredients, alternating with bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Remove from pan and cool.

title: eroscom pollo(chicken with rice)
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook until chicken is done, 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.

title: franklin pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add beaten eggs.
Add 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt. Mix remaining flour; add cherries, pineapple and broken pecans.
Stir mixture into batter; add vanilla and pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Heat jello and pineapple over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Remove from heat and cool. Stir in cottage cheese. Fold in Cool Whip and mix in pecans. Pour into a 1-quart glass container and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cherry-chocolate cake and frosting
directions: Prepare cake according to box directions; add pie filling and bake as directed.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and water until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice.
Pack apples into hot jars. Leave 1 inch headroom.
Fill with syrup.
Process in hot water bath; quarts 20 minutes, pints 15 minutes.
One quart makes 9-inch pie.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix jello, crushed pineapple (drained, but reserve juice), apples and bananas.
Congeal.
Mix 1/2 pineapple juice, sugar, egg and flour in saucepan.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package.
Add cream cheese.
Stir in egg mixture and pour over set jello.

title: kraut salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingred. and mix well.
Heat water, vinegar, oil and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over kraut mixture and mix well, chill.

title: quick potato soup
directions: Combine ingredients as listed.
Heat thoroughly and serve hot. Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Put water, chicken, onion and parsley in a large pan.
Bring to boil; add bouillon granules and dissolve.
Add cream of chicken soup and 1 can water.
Drop in frozen noodles and stir to separate.
Simmer 50 minutes.

title: yankee salad
directions: In large skillet, on low heat, cook onions in oil and butter for 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes; cook an additional 3 minutes.
Spread flour in pan; lightly brown in oven. Sift the mustard, salt and white pepper together; sprinkle over onions and tomatoes.
Stir in with wooden spoon.
Add Madeira; increase heat slightly.
Stir until wine is absorbed and mixture is smooth and thick.
Add 1 cup of hot stock slowly, stirring to scrape bottom of pan.
Transfer to large kettle (stockpot).
Add remainder of hot stock; simmer for 30 minutes.

title: hurricane cake
directions: Spread pecans and coconut in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box and pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, margarine and vanilla together; drop by spoonfuls on cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, oil and nectar together; next add 1 egg at a time.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour in oven.
Mix 1 cup powdered sugar and juice of 1 lemon.
Pour over cake while still warm to make a glaze.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, saving liquid.
Cook bacon, until crisp, in a large saucepan.
Lower heat and add onion. Stir over low heat for 1 minute.
Add flour, celery salt, pepper and 3/4 teaspoon salt. Stir in water and clam liquid.
Add potatoes.
Bring to a boil. Cover and boil gently 12 minutes or until tender.
Add milk and half and half and remaining 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Heat to just below boiling point.
Add butter and clams.
Cook 1 minute more and serve.
Makes 6 servings or 4 main course servings.

title: barbecue pork
directions: Rinse pork shoulder, vinegar, soup mix, bay leaves, granulated garlic, and hot sauce place in crock pot and cover with cold water.
Cook all day on low heat, until meat falls off bone. Pull pork and mix with your favorite barbecue sauce.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: venison chili
directions: In large saucepan, brown venison in oil.
Add soup; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients except beans; simmer for 1 hour.
Add beans; simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: reunion casserole
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in 1 cup cheese, green pepper, corn, soup, tomato sauce, olives, garlic, salt and noodles.
Put all in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes longer.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until soft and drain. Add 1 quart milk and heat. Season to taste.
Work the butter into the flour.

Add the egg and 1/4 cup milk, using enough milk to make mixture thin enough to drop into the hot milk. Drop by teaspoonfuls into the hot milk. Cover the saucepan and cook about 10 minutes. Serve at once.

title: banana chocolate chip cake
directions: At low speed, cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda and sour cream.
On low speed add bananas.
Mix lightly.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: scottie's spaghetti
directions: Boil water, then you put the spaghetti in it. Then you cook it. Put that sauce on it. Then you eat it.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with buttermilk and vanilla.
Fold in bananas and chopped pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain and add oregano, onion and chili powder.
Stir in 1 can tomato sauce.
Press crescent rolls in 9-inch pie plate.
Add hamburger sauce and top with cheese.
Bake at 425° until crust is brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple in cake pan.
Spoon pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Place dabs of oleo over cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey wings and yellow rice
directions: Wash wings in saltwater. Season to taste. Cook until done. Remove wings from broth. Add rice and cream of chicken soup. When rice is fluffy, remove from oven. Add turkey wings. Serve with green vegetables. You can also use oxtails instead of turkey wings.

title: iced apple tea
directions: Remove boiling water from heat; let tea bags brew for 5 minutes.
Remove.
Add allspice, honey and apple juice and simmer over low heat until honey is blended, about 1 minute.
Chill. Serve over ice with lemon slices for garnish.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Split and lightly toast muffins.
Spread with tomato sauce. Sprinkle with oregano and garlic to taste.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Top with onion, pepperoni and Mozzarella.
Broil on low until heated through and cheese melts.
Scatter chopped olives over the top before serving.
Serves 6.

title: bread stuffing balls
directions: Mix ingredients in one cup of broth; form into loose 2-inch balls.
Arrange in pan and add remaining broth.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carrot congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups of boiling water and stir.
Let cool 5 minutes.
Add crushed pineapple, carrot (grated fine) and chopped pecans.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch glass dish or 4 cup salad mold.
Refrigerate.

title: carrots ambrossienes
directions: Combine all ingredients except marshmallows and chill several hours.
Add marshmallows before serving.
This is great with baked ham or turkey.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, cream of tartar and salt in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Very slowly, add to egg whites in mixing bowl, beat at high speed until peaks form.
Add vanilla.

title: baked apples
directions: Cook on high until juicy, covered. Remove top and turn to low. Cook 45 minutes.

title: cream pound cake
directions: Cream together eggs and sugar. Add in flour, baking powder and salt. Stir in whipping cream.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: hot taco dip(microwave)
directions: Spread cream cheese on the bottom of a glass micro-safe deep dish. Pour in the chili with beans. Spread salsa on top of the chili.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Dip chips into the dip.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Layer in a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish the cooked spaghetti noodles and a layer of spaghetti sauce.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream; spread over.
Layer spaghetti noodles and more sauce. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and sugar.
Add the egg, sour cream, vanilla and nutmeg.
Beat into a smooth thin batter.
Blend in the apples and pour into the unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with topping made of brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and butter.
Place oven temperature back at 400° and brown for about 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Set aside.
Take softened margarine and cover bottom and sides of Bundt cake pan.
Place coconut in bottom of pan.
Mix pineapple and juice with sugar. Pour in cake pan, then pour in cake mix.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven.
Let cake set in pan for 10 minutes to soak up juice before turning out.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix ingredients thoroughly and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 2 hours.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: The night before, grease a 12 cup Bundt pan or tube pan.
Put in frozen rolls.

title: hearty navy bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in large Dutch oven. Cover with water 2-inches above beans. Cover and let stand 8 hours. Drain. Combine beans, water, onion, garlic, ham and bay leaf in pan. Bring to boil. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 2 hours. Stir in carrots, salt and pepper. Simmer 40 minutes or until beans are tender. Remove bay leaf and discard. Remove ham hocks and shred meat, discarding fat and gristle. Return meat to pan. Serves 8.

title: rice
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Add onion, saute until transparent.
In casserole
dish,
mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, until small amount dropped in cold water forms a hard ball.
In mixer, beat egg whites until stiff peak forms.
Continue beating while pouring hot syrup in a thin stream into egg whites.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture holds its shape.
Fold in nuts.

title: yams hawaiian style
directions: Slice yams into 1/2-inch thick pieces (or may be mashed). Combine with pineapple, butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Microwave on High 4 minutes. Stir. Sprinkle top with pecans and brown sugar. Microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes or until dish is hot and topping is melted.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and line a pizza pan.
Bake on pizza pan for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla extract; spread on baked cookie dough.
Add fruit of your choice (peaches, strawberries, bananas, cherry or blueberry pie filling, mandarin oranges, grapes, pineapple, kiwi or fruit cocktail).

title: boeuf melange
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in casserole.
Mix flour and bread crumbs together and stir into casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 3 hours.
Serves 4.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Place butter in a small saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat, stir in sour cream and sugar; cool mixture to lukewarm. Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir in sour cream mixture and eggs.
Combine flour and salt, gradually add to yeast mixture, mixing well; cover dough and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix sugar, Crisco and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs.
Then add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips and oatmeal.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet with tablespoon.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes about four dozen nice puffy cookies.

title: chocolate amaretto trifle
directions: Combine pudding, milk and Amaretto; stir until thick.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.

title: bavarian cheese cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on box and pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch floured and greased pan. In another bowl, blend remaining ingredients, then pour on top of other cake batter. Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Mix together ingredients. Simmer on medium low heat until hot. Serve with grilled cheese sandwich, using wheat bread and 2% shredded cheese, and apple slices.

title: quick chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Slather mustard evenly over chicken, then pour teriyaki sauce evenly over all.
Sprinkle with bacon bits; cover with cheese. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: Drain pears, reserving juice.
In bowl, mash pears and stir in cream cheese (softened) until well blended.
In small saucepan, bring pear juice to boil.
Pour into a clean medium bowl.
Add gelatin and water; stir in pears.
Whisk in topping.
Pour mixture into a mold.
Chill overnight.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
When chicken is done, tear in little pieces. Roll out crescent rolls flat.
Put pieces of chicken and cheese on rolls and roll up.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Put one can of soup and half can of water in pot and stir until smooth. Add cheese to mixture when stirring.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 350 degrees until rolls are done.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Soak sliced cucumbers in 1 tablespoon salt and water.
Soak 1 hour, then drain and add sugar, vinegar, celery seed and turmeric. Cover and leave in container overnight.
Stir about 2 or 3 times. Next morning, uncover and mix well; put in freezer bags.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Boil noodles until tender (do not overcook), then drain.
Chop vegetables and garlic; saute in oleo (all except parsley) and add flour and cook 5 minutes.
Add half and half and Velveeta cheese. Cook until bubbles; pour into one extra large or two medium size casserole dishes.
Bake 15 minutes.
Add Parmesan and cook another 15 minutes.

title: teething cookies
directions: Break the eggs into a bowl.

Stir in one direction until creamy. Add the sugar. Continue stirring in the same direction. Gradually stir the flour into the mixture and continue stirring until mixture is stiff. Roll out dough with rolling pin between 2 lightly floured sheets of wax paper to a thickness of 3/4-inch. Use a drinking glass and a salt shaker to cut out doughnut shaped cookies.
Place cookies on a lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Let formed cookies stand overnight (10 to 12 hours).
Bake in preheated oven at 325° until lightly brown and hard. This recipe makes approximately 12 durable and relatively crumbproof teething biscuits.

title: greek noodles
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer slow for 2 or 3 hours. When sauce is ready, cook noodles.
Drain and pour sauce over noodles.
Mix or sprinkle grated mild Cheddar cheese into noodles and sauce.

title: broccoli and potato salad
directions: Cut cooked broccoli into florets and place in large bowl.
Add potatoes and celery.
Season well.
Mix vinegar, oil, salt and pepper together in small bowl.
Pour over broccoli and toss to evenly coat.
Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve warm.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, egg, water and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients; drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Add sugar; cut in shortening.
Add yeast, then buttermilk.
Knead; place in refrigerator.
Make out into biscuits as needed; do not allow to rise before baking.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 minutes.

title: cold macaroni salad
directions: Combine last 8 ingredients and add to cooked drained macaroni. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: layered taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix and follow directions for water/simmering on envelope.
Peel and puree avocado with about a tablespoon of lemon juice.
If desired, green chilies may be added to this mixture.
Shred cheeses.
Dice tomato.
Thinly slice onions and greens.

Layer the following in a flat plate: refried beans, avocado mixture, ground beef (turkey), green chilies, sour cream, diced tomato, sharp Cheddar cheese, Monterey Jack cheese, olives and green onions.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: nail soup
directions: Cut potatoes, carrots, onions, celery and okra in small pieces, about 1/2 inch lengths.
Put in 6-quart soup kettle. Cover with water and bring to boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add cabbage and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add leftovers, up to 1/2 cup of each: peas, corn, green beans, hominy, rice, etc., tomato soup, tomatoes, bouillon cubes and seasoned salt to taste.
Add water up to 5 or 5 1/2-quart measure.
Bring to boil and simmer on lowest heat for 30 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream cheese with mixer, adding 1 egg at a time, then add sugar and vanilla.
Pour into pan (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; put on topping and return to oven for 5 more minutes.

title: beef corn dandy
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; drain off grease.
Add corn and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Melt cheese over top just before serving.

title: frozen lemonade punch
directions: In a blender, combine lemonade concentrate, crushed pineapple and strawberries.
Blend at low speed for 15 to 30 seconds until smooth.
Chill.

title: tortilla chip chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together, using only half of crumbled tortilla chips.
Pour into casserole that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cover top with remaining tortilla chips and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.
You can make two and freeze one.

title: crab dip
directions: Heat soup; cool some.
Dissolve gelatine in 3 tablespoons water; add to soup.
Add mayonnaise, celery and onion.
Stir. Pour into mold.
Put in refrigerator to set.
Before serving, turn onto platter.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine flour, butter and brown sugar. Blend with mixer until particles are fine.
Stir in walnuts. Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Press remainder in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken and cut into small pieces. Saute pepper, onion and garlic.
In separate pot cook rice in chicken stock until tender and liquid is absorbed.
Let set in pot 20 minutes after cooking.
Stir in salt, pepper and saffron. Gently stir in peas and sauteed mixture.
Place rice in casserole dish; add chicken pieces on top.
Bake 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with Jack cheese.
Bake until light golden brown.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions; cover with boiling water and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain.
Bring rest of ingredients to a boil; add pepper mix and boil 10 minutes.
Fill pint jars and seal.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in food processor for about 30 seconds.
Chill and serve with fruit.

title: bouillie lait(cajun milk pudding)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and enough water to make a paste.
Add flour and sugars to hot milk; stir and simmer.
When mixture thickens, add vanilla.
If thicker mixture is desired, add a little cornstarch, sugar and water.
You may also add coconut.
This may be served separately as a pudding.
